title: charleston soup
directions: Brown shank and bone in oven.
Then put in huge pot.
Add 1 unpeeled onion with 2 cloves stuck in it, 1 quart tomatoes and 6 quarts water.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Take out meat and onion.
Discard onion.
Add vegetables and garlic.
Let simmer 5 to 6 hours. Season when adding vegetables.
Add 1/4 teaspoon thyme last hour. Take meat from bone and marrow.
Cut up and add to soup.
Cook 1/2 hour.
If you need more liquid, add tomato juice.

title: strawberries and almonds
directions: Combine the berries, extract, sugar and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Let the mixture stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.

title: tex mex appetizers
directions: Layer on pizza pan in the following order:
beans, sour cream with taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, onions, olives and cheese. Chill and serve with nacho chips.

title: refrigerator pastry
directions: Blend or sift together flour and salt. Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in finely 1 pound shortening and sprinkle with cold water. Add the water gradually, mixing lightly with a fork until all flour is dampened. Turn dough onto a large piece of wax paper and form into a ball. Wrap securely. Store in refrigerator until needed. To use, cut off portion required, roll out and use. This pastry may be kept refrigerated for 3 to 4 weeks and used as needed. Keep it securely wrapped to prevent drying. It makes 3 double pie crusts or 6 shells. It is a real time saver.

title: salad nicoise* * * * *
directions: In Luxemburg City, there was a restaurant by the name of Stuff's (pronounced Stoof's) that made this wonderful onion soup. They served it as a first course in a large tureen with the bread and cheese on top.
We always followed it with Coq au Vin, which was a mistake.
We would eat so much of the soup, we could hardly eat the chicken, but we would manage and go away so full we were miserable.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Prepare the mashed potatoes.
Season to taste.
Beat egg yolks into mashed potatoes until well mixed.
Stir in cheese, onion, green pepper and celery salt.
Whip egg whites into soft peaks and fold into potato mixture.
Spoon into a well-buttered casserole dish about 1 1/2-quart size.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley sprig.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: *Or 1 large bag strawberries.

title: elaine's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a 2-quart jar, combine all ingredients, except eggs, and mix well.
Add eggs.
Cover and refrigerate.
Marinate for 3 days before serving for best color and flavor.
Serve with hot mustard.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Cut up fish and simmer with all other ingredients except clams, mussels, shrimp and scallops for about 1/2 hour; add the clams, mussels, shrimp and scallops and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Melt cheese.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Add eggs and macaroni.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 50 minutes until knife comes out clean.
(I serve with chili sauce.)

title: jane's cheese potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes in microwave until slightly frozen.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons melted butter and onion over potatoes.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper potatoes.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle crushed cornflakes mixed with 3 tablespoons butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cover with foil if corn flakes get too brown.
Can be made day ahead. Wonderful for a crowd!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans and pie shell.
Put pecans into the pie shell and pour the mixture over.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chili con carne
directions: In heavy skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Before serving, remove bay leaf.
Makes 4 serving.
Adding thin spaghetti is also good.

title: mexican trash basket soup
directions: Do not drain any of the vegetables. Place onion, Rotel tomatoes, green chilies, pinto beans, corn, lima beans, onion soup mix, and celery in large pot and simmer. Cook for 2 hours. During the last 30 minutes add zucchini, sausage, and olives. Serve over cubed Monterrey Jack cheese.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Beat steak to tenderize.
Flour, salt and pepper steak.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Drain.
Place steak pieces into casserole dish.
Add soup mix, mushroom soup, milk and mushrooms.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: plum cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl together.
Stir with a spoon until blended.
Generously grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan and pour in cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brunch strata
directions: Use donut cutter and cut "donuts" and holes out of bread. Save donuts and holes; put the rest of scraps on bottom of a 9 x 13 sprayed baking dish.
Put cheese, meat and broccoli in layers. Mix eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard together.
Place "donuts" and holes on the top of dish and pour milk mixture over. Refrigerate overnight and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: willie's chili
directions: Select a 3 to 4 pound chuck or rump pot roast. Trim off excess fat; heat in large skillet or Dutch oven.
When you have about 2 tablespoons melted fat, remove trimmings.
For rich brown, roll pot roast in flour; brown slowly on all sides in hot fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Add more water if needed to prevent sticking.
Add small whole onions, potatoes and carrots the last 45 minutes of cooking.
Thicken liquid for pot-roast gravy, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Enjoy!

title: quick apple pie(no crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate until serving time. Serves 6.

title: french cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Bake in jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inches) at 375° for 15 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing while warm.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers over pudding. Spread remaining pudding over crackers.
Cover with another layer of crackers.
Spread Chocolate Topping over all this (recipe follows).

title: chili using deer meat
directions: In bowl, combine chili powder, flour, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper and oregano; mix well. Brown burger; add salt, pepper and onion. Cook 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and beans.
Add mixture in bowl; simmer 1 hour. Add tomato juice, if you like.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans; let cook.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 400°.

title: parmesan vegetable sticks
directions: Bring water, onion and chicken bouillon to a boil.
Stir until bouillon is dissolved.
Add carrots and celery.
Cover and cook about 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Increase heat to 350°.
Top casserole with bread crumbs. Bake until top is browned.

title: improved chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix together peanut butter, marshmallow cream, butter and sugar.
Shape into eggs.
Freeze for 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Boil and mash peeled potatoes.
Add onion, butter, seasoning and milk.
Whip until smooth.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Fold the cheese into the whipped cream and spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be mixed and refrigerated overnight, but increase baking time by 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix and bake in uncooked pie shell until set.
Bake at 375°.

title: cream cheese pound cake 1
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla, beat well. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition. Stir in flour. Spoon mixture into greased 10 in. tube pan and bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter apple salad
directions: Mix together.
Add apples, raisins, marshmallows, bananas and celery.

title: calico meringues
directions: Beat eggs and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar slowly and continue to beat until stiff.
Fold in candy gently.
Place on a greased and floured cookie sheet (even for Teflon).
They do not spread, so may be placed close together.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Watch carefully so they do not darken.

title: billie's banana split salad
directions: Mix pie filling, Eagle Brand milk, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges (drained and chopped).
Add pecans and Cool Whip; mix well.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Serves approximately 12 to 15.

title: tri level brownies
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tamale-hominy casserole
directions: Cut onion and green pepper into chunks.
Saute until limp. Drain hominy.
Peel the tamale and cut into 6 to 8 chunks.
Gently combine all 4 ingredients.
Put into a baking dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and roll into small balls, about 1 teaspoonful. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cook to boil.
Remove from heat; cool until lukewarm.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating vigorously until mixture firms (about 2 minutes).
Stir in nuts.
Spread into 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan and chill.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: strawberry tarts
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into flour.
Work with the combination until it clings together in a ball.
Chill well in the refrigerator.
Roll cream cheese pastry out into a thin layer on a lightly floured board.
Cut into small circles.
Place a small amount of strawberry jam on each.
Fold pastry over and crimp edges together with a fork.
Brush tops with milk and sprinkle lightly with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar and finely chopped nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 12 tarts.

title: apple stuffed chicken with applejack sauce
directions: Put wine, applejack and shallots in a pan and cook until reduced by half.
Add chicken broth and reduce again by half.
Add cream and 2/3 of apples; simmer for about 5 minutes.
Salt may be added, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 cups.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Beat all ingredients and bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: In the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, which has been well buttered, place broccoli.
Next, chop chicken into bite size pieces and place on top of broccoli layer.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour in greased cooking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, Eagle Brand and lemon and pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Mix cream of tartar, sugar and egg whites.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop; set aside.
Pour cooking oil into large mixing bowl;
add
sugar
and eggs and beat.
Sift flour with salt, soda	and
baking
powder.
Gradually
add flour to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Gently fold in chopped apples. Grease a 10-inch tube
pan and line with waxed paper;
pour in batter. Bake at 350°
for
one hour or until done.	When cake is cool, remove from pan and drizzle on Sugar Glaze.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Sift together cake mix and jello, dry.
Add one egg at a time, 1 cup of frozen strawberries, 1 cup flaked coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake in three layers at 350°.

title: nine egg pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream sugar and margarine, about 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix in flour.
Beat good.
Add flavorings.
Pour into tube pan and bake approximately 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Have eggs and margarine at room temperature.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and add onions to bacon grease.
Fry onions until tender.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt, vinegar and bacon, broken into small pieces.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Grease 4-quart pan. Mix all together with the four different kinds of beans.
Bake covered for 30 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: w. w. turkey lasagna
directions: Heat oil. Add turkey and onion. Cook, stirring as needed, until the turkey is browned, about 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano and sugar. Bring to boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, until the flavors are blended, about 5 minutes. Spoon 1/3 of the sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9 baking pan. Top with 3 noodles. Spread with half cottage cheese. Top with 3 more noodles. Repeat the layering once more, ending with sauce. Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake, covered, 1 hour. Uncover. Bake 10 minutes more at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers.
Best if prepared one day ahead.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring, water and vinegar.
Add coconut.
Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until a golden brown.
Makes 1 pie.

title: sinful chocolate squares
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add chocolate syrup and flour.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish and cook 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix
all
dry
ingredients;
add water, egg and butter. Beat a little; pour in well-greased pan.
Bake 450° for about 25 minutes.

title: gun barrel
directions: Use a Martini glass.
(Shooter) Mix Kurant vodka, Triple Sec cranberry juice and lime juice.
Serve chilled and up.

title: cabbage and ground beef casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Place butter in custard cup.
Microwave on High for 30 to 40 seconds until melted.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes. Separate shrimp and place in 9 or 10-inch diameter dish.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp evenly.
Cover tightly.
Microwave 5 to 8 minutes until shrimp are opaque, stirring every 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over noodles or some form of pasta.

title: mrs. rock's potatoes
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Freezes well if frozen before cooked.
Makes large amount.
Usually put in two casseroles, 1 to serve and 1 to freeze for later.

title: spice bread
directions: Butter a bread pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Heat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks and brown sugar in mixer until very light and fluffy. Add spices and flour (mixture will be stiff).
Beat egg whites until firm and peaked.
Spoon half of the egg whites into the mixture and when well blended, add the other half with the baking powder.
Mix.
Spread batter into well-greased bread pan.
Butter a piece of aluminum foil and cover the batter with it.
Batter will rise considerably.
Bake 1 hour without opening oven, then turn oven to 300° for 15 minutes.
Knife inserted should come out clean.
Slice thin and serve with butter.

title: hamburger-dorito casserole
directions: Combine 3 soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat until hot! Brown ground meat, bell pepper and onion.
Mix ground meat mixture and soup together.
In large casserole, layer half Doritos, meat mixture and then grated cheese.
Repeat layers (Doritos, ground meat and then cheese).
Cover with foil.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal drop cookies(good!)
directions: Cook in large saucepan for 1 1/2 minutes then mix thoroughly first 3 ingredients.
Stir while cooking.
Set off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Braise tenderloin cubes in butter and garlic for approximately 2 minutes in skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef broth, mushrooms and onion. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes until liquid is less than 1/4 cup. Add dry Bearnaise mix and sour cream. Mix well. Serve immediately over wild rice or flat noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Mix chicken with other ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. turner's cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add egg, oleo, oil and vanilla.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Boil juices and cinnamon.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except orange, to boiling juices and simmer 5 more minutes, uncovered.
Makes 20 cups.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Sift flour, measure and add baking powder and salt. Sift again.
Cut in shortening.
Blend until mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Stir in enough milk to make soft dough.
Turn dough out on light floured board.
Knead lightly, about 1/2
minute.
Pat or roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 to 16 (2-inch) biscuits or makes 24 small ones.

title: date and nut torte
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Mix baking powder and cracker crumbs.
Add to sugar, then mix in dates and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350°.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon bean mixture into a lightly greased 2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread dressing(10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well and stir in celery and onions.
Heat bacon drippings in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet in preheating oven.
Add 1 tablespoon bacon drippings to batter and mix well.
Pour batter into very hot skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn cornbread out onto a plate to cool.
Crumble cornbread into large mixing bowl and add stuffing mix and sage; set aside.
Place soup in a medium saucepan and gradually stir in broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated.
Pour over crumb mixture; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Add 3 to 4 teaspoons to cup of boiling water.
Ready to drink.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour into graham cracker pie shells.
Top with cherry pie filling. Makes two pies.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine butter and seasonings; blend thoroughly.
Shape butter mixture into a stick; cover and freeze about 45 minutes or until firm.
Place each piece of chicken between 2 pieces of wax paper. Flatten each chicken piece to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Cut stick of butter mixture into six pats; place a pat in center of each chicken breast.
Fold long sides of chicken over butter; fold ends over and secure with a wooden pick. Dredge each piece of chicken in flour; dip in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry chicken in 1 inch hot oil (350°).
Cook 5 minutes on each side or until browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Form into balls and roll in sugar; press with fork and cook at 350°.

title: baked pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown the pork chops on both sides in a skillet and place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix the bread crumbs, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and pepper; place on pork chops.
Blend the soup and 1/3 cup water; pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pork is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brussels sprouts parmesan
directions: Remove the outer wilted leaves from sprouts; trim stems.
In a medium saucepan, combine sprouts and water.
Bring to boiling over high heat; reduce to low and steam 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries; add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Pour dry pudding mix over fruit cocktail and pineapple (do not drain).
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: peach slush
directions: In a blender, blend yogurt and peaches.
With blender running, add ice cubes, one at a time, blending to form slush.
Makes 3 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in 10-inch Bundt pan (well-greased).
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar and pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan and invert on a platter.
Break off pieces and enjoy.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion until soft, not brown.
Add pepper.
Cook until soft.
Add celery and tomato, and paste if using it.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and add seasonings.
Simmer until shrimp is done, about 8 minutes.
Do not overcook shrimp.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease tins, no flour. Bake at 325°
or for glass 25° lower.

title: crab meat delight
directions: Soften cheese and mix the first 4 ingredients together. Spread on a shallow 10-inch plate.
Drain and shred crabmeat mix with last 2 ingredients.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: english toffee
directions: Butter 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet well.
Toast almonds 10 minutes at 300° (watch carefully not to burn).
Combine in saucepan, butter, sugar and almonds, stirring constantly, to 300°. Pour on cookie sheet; sprinkle on top semi-sweet chocolate chips; spread with spatula until melted.
Sprinkle
on slivered almonds when cool completely and break up like peanut brittle.

title: bubble bread
directions: Place frozen dinner rolls in greased round angel food cake pan.
Mix topping with remainder of ingredients.
Pour over rolls. Place in oven.
Let rise overnight.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Put drained peas in long Pyrex dish.
Melt together 1/2 stick margarine and the Velveeta cheese.
Pour over peas.
Crust Ritz crackers and mix with another 1/2 stick of melted margarine.
Put this on top of pea and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all of the ingredients except the sugar, cinnamon and blueberries. Blend on low speed for 1 minute, then beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour half of the batter into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

Combine the sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of this mixture over the batter, followed by half of the blueberries. Repeat this procedure, beginning with the rest of the batter once. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serves 12.

title: lowcountry or low country coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the oil, eggs (one at a time) and cake mix alternately with sour cream and water (last), mixing well after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Turn out on plate. Drizzle glaze over hot cake.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Using a mixer, cream together the cream cheese and salmon. Add other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or on party rye rounds.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream oil, butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, salt and soda together.
Add to egg mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk. Add boiling water last.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Cut bread in round shapes by using inverted wine glass. Combine grated eggs, mayo and salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mixture on bread rounds.
Garnish with a slice of black olive.

title: spinach balls(makes 70 balls)
directions: Mix well, form into small balls 1 to 2 inches in diameter. Place on cookie sheet; freeze.
Place in plastic bags in freezer until needed.
Bake frozen in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno buttermilk corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 8 inch pan.
In mixing bowl combine dry ingredients.
Stir in corn, onion, peppers and cheese. Combine oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Turn into pan.
Bake until lightly brown. Let set
5 - 10 minutes before cutting.

title: white texas cake
directions: Orange, honey, nutmeg and cloves team up in these buttery tender, soft drop cookies.

title: jello pie
directions: Chill Pet milk.
Whip Pet milk.
Mix Jell-O, sugar and water together.
Add to Pet milk slowly.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 3 pies.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together (except margarine). Pour into an ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from the oven. Pour the melted margarine over the baked cornbread. Let stand until it has been absorbed.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook
spaghetti
according to package
and
drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti and stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs. Form
spaghetti mixture into crust in a
buttered
10-inch	pie plate.
In skillet, cook ground beef, onion,
and
green pepper until vegetables are tender and
meat
is
browned.
Drain fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato	paste,	sugar,	oregano and garlic
salt.
Heat.
Spread cottage
cheese
over
bottom
of crust.
Fill pie with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: salad supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch oiled dish.
Allow to almost congeal and add drained pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top and return to refrigerator to completely congeal.
Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese and spread over congealed Jell-O.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Return to refrigerator and chill.
Mix pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar, flour and eggs in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Chill.
Spread over Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or similar.
Drain cherries. Dip cherries, holding by stem or, if they don't have a stem, use a toothpick.
Place dipped cherries in small candy paper cups or a piece of foil or wax paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chop ham very fine.
Mix ham with other ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Nuts, optional.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and eggs.
Cool.
Add macaroni, eggs, onion, celery and sweet relish together.
Mix in mayonnaise.

title: magic crescent puffs
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Separate dough into 16 triangles. Dip marshmallow into melted butter, then cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place marshmallows in wide end of triangle.
Fold corners over marshmallow and roll towards point, completely covering marshmallows and squeeze edges of dough to seal.
Dip pointed side in butter and place buttered side down in a greased deep muffin pan with points tucked under.
Repeat with all marshmallows.
Place pans on cookie sheet during baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While hot, drizzle with icing.

title: sue's corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon in a Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove bacon and reserve 3 tablespoons drippings in Dutch oven.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in reserved drippings until tender, then add potatoes and water.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Stir in milk, corn, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle each serving with crumbled bacon.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Be sure to spray pans.

title: butterscotch skedaddles
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler over very low heat or in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes on 50% power.
Stir in noodles and peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef; add onions, celery and 1 cup hot water. Cover tightly and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts which have been rinsed.
Combine soy sauce, 2 tablespoons water and flour in jar with lid and shake well.
Add to meat mixture and continue cooking for 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened (add extra water if mixture is too dry). Serve with La Choy noodles or rice.

title: souper spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Add Ragu sauce and mushroom soup.
Cook spaghetti according to directions and add to hamburg, sauce and soup.
Spread in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place pepperoni evenly on top.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 40 minutes, covered at 350°, then 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt into a bowl. In another bowl, beat margarine (or butter) and sugar together until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add the flour mixture, little by little, beating until blended.
Shape batter into 1-inch balls and place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip the bottom of a glass in sugar and flatten the cookies.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until the edges start to brown.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to boiling; add Jell-O.
Mix well and set aside.
Prepare Dream Whip following package directions, then add cream cheese and beat together.
Cut angel food cake into slices.

title: linda's sweet potato casserole
directions: Save liquid from potatoes.
Mix 1 stick butter, eggs and sugar.
Mash potatoes; add mixture and 1/2 cup of liquid from potatoes.
Mix brown sugar and stick of butter with corn flakes. Place potato mixture in Corning Ware and sprinkle with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: kari's burgundy meatballs
directions: Mix meat, onion, allspice, egg, dried crumbs, cornstarch and milk well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown meatballs on all sides in 1/4 cup oil.
Transfer to platter and set aside.
Mix flour and water well, then stir into fat left in pan.
Stir in beef bouillon cubes and cook until smooth.
Add 1 cup Burgundy and meatballs.
Simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with picks from a chafing dish.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Add sugar, vinegar, catsup, soy sauce and juice to heavy pan and bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixture all at once, while stirring constantly.
Mixture will thicken and become translucent. Add pineapple chunks.

title: sweet and tart
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugars.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Chill until ready to serve.
Core and slice the Granny Smith apples. Sprinkle with Fruit-Fresh.
Serve with dip.

title: mom's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Add parsley, eggs, onion and celery.

title: black steer's chocolate mint pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, melted chocolate and peppermint extract.
Beat until well mixed. Pour into crust and chill overnight.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add garlic and ground beef.
Stir until meat loses its red color.
Pour off excess fat.
Add beans with their liquid, onion and green pepper.
Stir in Hunt's tomato sauce, salt and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chili is desired thickness, about 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chinese rice
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Fry bacon in skillet; crumble bacon. Cook onions until done.
Scramble eggs.
Mix rice, bacon, onions and eggs.
Add enough soy sauce to make brown.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: broccoli-rice bake
directions: Cook
broccoli	according to package directions; drain. Cook onions in oleo until soft, not brown.
Stir in rice, soup and broccoli;
place
in
buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Take off bone in small pieces.
Mix melted margarine, both kinds of soup, chicken and water chestnuts.
Put one pack of crushed crackers in a large bowl.
Pour the chicken mixture over the crackers.
Then cover the top with crackers with a little margarine.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour, spices, baking soda, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, buttermilk and flour mixture alternately.
Add dates or raisins, nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 30 minutes, or until top is browned.
Can be served plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy, easy cake(chocolate)
directions: Put oleo, cocoa, oil
and water in a pan and bring to a boil. Sift plain	flour.	Add sugar into a large mixing bowl. Pour cocoa mixture
into
this.
Mix
eggs,
soda, vanilla and buttermilk in a separate bowl.
Add to first mixture.
Bake in a long pan in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
After cake has been baking 15 minutes, start the icing.

title: ham 'n cheese chowder
directions: Place 1/2 cup water and salt in small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and reduce heat.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Set potatoes aside.
Add enough water to potato liquid to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a 3-quart Dutch oven.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Stir in milk and potato liquid.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is bubbly and slightly thickened.
Add cooked potatoes and ham; heat gently.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Top with croutons, if desired.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: The Old South Fork Union Grammar School (proclaimed on the sign in big letters) was a 3 room building made from cement blocks.
It was torn down in the 1950's to make room for the new school building.
The old building was still so strong, the bulldozer could hardly knock it down.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: Saute ground beef and remove all grease.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not grease. Spread apple pie filling over cherry filling, then spread dry cake mix over pie fillings.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts. Cut margarine into small pieces and spread over cake mix and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes, until bubbly and light brown. After cooled, you can top, if desired.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with potato chips or bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: pepperoni pizzazz
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.

Meanwhile, combine 2 1/3 c. spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, pepperoni, green pepper, onion, parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes in a bowl. Drain pasta, add to sauce mixture and mix well. Transfer to a greased 3 qt. baking dish. Combine the tomato sauce and remaining spaghetti sauce; pour over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered 5-10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients into a large glass bowl in the order listed (top to bottom).

title: baked corn
directions: Beat egg in bowl.
Add mixture of sugar and flour.
Mix well. Stir in corn, milk and salt.
Spoon into greased baking dish; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 2.

title: dallas dip
directions: Fry the hamburger and sausage together.
Drain well.
Put back in large pan; add all other ingredients. Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, vanilla, beaten eggs and sugar in a bowl.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each cupcake pan lined with papers.
Fill each approximately half full and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After cheesecakes are cooled, spoon cherries on and enjoy.

title: blueberry refrigerator cake
directions: Mix topping, sour cream or cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread on each cake layer.
Spoon blueberry pie filling between cake layers and on top layer.
Place in cake saver and refrigerate until all is served.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix and divide into 2 logs and roll in crushed pecans.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until thick.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix oleo, flour, sugar and salt;
sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until topping is golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in wheat germ.
Add all remaining ingredients and beat well.
Place in an oiled 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Yields 1 loaf (16 slices), approximately 130 calories per serving (1 slice).

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat well and then rinse in colander under hot water to rinse away excess fat.
Put hamburger in large pot and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Turn fire to low, cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Drain spinach and squeeze out all moisture.
Add all ingredients.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with tinfoil. Spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Remove foil lining and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops, pat dry and sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Next, with a sharp filet or paring knife, trim off excess fat.
Cut a 1 inch slit into the middle of the front of the pork chop from side to side.
Use the slit to cut a pocket into the pork chop from the bone to about 1/2 inch from the end of the meat.
Your butcher will do this for you.
Next, in a large bowl mix ground pork with all remaining ingredients until all is blended well.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Stuff the pork mixture into the pockets of the pork chops.
Be generous and stuff it in until pork chop expands in the center. If there is any stuffing left, just make them into balls and cook with the pork chops.
Next, spray an oven pan with a vegetable coating and place pork chops into pan with 1 cup water and cover.
Place in oven for 35 minutes, remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Heat until cheese melts.
Spread on bread and broil until bubbly.
Freezes well.
Reheat in a 400° oven for a few minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
This keeps for a full week.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: garden rice
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic and carrots in butter in a Dutch oven. Add broth and other ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Put in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cut while warm.
Put butter on knife to cut.

title: grandma kelii's  oyster sauce ribs
directions: Boil ribs with ginger for about 1 hour over low heat.
Mix remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Drain ribs and pour sauce over hot ribs.
Charcoal broil or bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook water and sugar until it spins a thread.
Put in peanuts and cook until they begin to pop.
Add butter and soda.
Pour onto large cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: nice and spicy puff batter
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until smooth and evenly blended.
Cover and chill at least one hour.
Thin if necessary with beer or milk.
This is a great batter for fried hard crabs, crab cakes or fish fillet/cakes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and salt together.
Add 1/2 cup milk and egg yolks. Blend these ingredients.
Add remaining 2 cups milk.
Heat mixture in double boiler, stirring occasionally, until mixture becomes thick.
Add vanilla. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can bake in Bundt pan or two loaf pans.

title: pork chops, rice creole
directions: Season pork chops well on both sides with salt and pepper. Brown well in hot skillet.
Remove chops and drain off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Slice 2 onions and brown with garlic, minced in the fat.
Add hot water to the pan and condensed tomato soup.
Add chopped green onion tops, if you have them (or use extra onion at point mentioned), diced celery, chopped green pepper, chopped parsley and raw rice.
Season with salt, pepper, bay leaf, thyme and marjoram.
Mix well and pour over chops in casserole.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat and rice are tender.
If rice becomes dry toward end of baking time, add a little hot water.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, stir together scalloped potatoes, seasoning mix, poultry seasoning and hot water until well combined.
Add soup; blend well.
Add potato slices, turkey, carrots, celery and onion, stirring until thoroughly mixed.
Spoon mixture into 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pears and add water to make 1 cup.
Add to jello.
Refrigerate until jelled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Mix 1/2 cup jello with Cool Whip and make shell in bowl. Refrigerate again if not stiff enough to form peaks.
Add diced pears to rest of jello and gently fold in center of shell.

title: killer bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Butter both surfaces; broil to toast lightly.
Mix well the mayonnaise, cheese and garlic. Spread mixture generously on both buttered surfaces.
Sprinkle lightly with finely chopped basil.
Broil until golden and bubbly. Slice in wedges and serve hot.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bag, add all ingredients. Close and shake.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes, or until done.
Garnish with parsley (optional).

title: my vegetable soup
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are done. Scramble ground beef and onion.
Add to vegetables and tomato soup.

title: plantation rice dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Turn into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove; cover and continue baking 15 minutes.
Serve with roast chicken, turkey or Cornish hen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, broth, chilies and pepper.
Set aside. Soften tortillas by dipping, one at a time, into hot oil.
Drain on paper towels and stack.

title: turkey bayou burgers
directions: Prepare hot coals for grilling.

Place the ground turkey in a bowl and mix well with the scallions, bell pepper, garlic, cilantro and spices. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Gently form into 4 patties. Grill patties over hot coals, 3-inches from heat, for about 5 to 6 minutes per side.
If desired, spread buns with mayonnaise-type dressing and top burgers with avocado slices. Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a bowl on low with a mixer.
Pour into crust; put in freezer overnight.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce.

title: microwave fiesta tamale pie
directions: Mix corn muffin mix, egg and milk until just moistened.
Set aside.
Mix ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic in square baking dish, 8 x 8-inch.
Microwave at High (100%) until meat loses pink color, 5 to 9 minutes, stirring once to break up beef. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, tomato paste, chili powder and salt.
Microwave at High (100%) until mixture thickens, 4 to 8 minutes.
Stir in olives.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat the milk, 1 cup sugar,
Dream Whip and cream cheese until thick and stands up in a peak.
(Takes about 8 to 10 minutes.)

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies and hot water in a small bowl.
Spread evenly in the bottom of crust.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl on medium speed of mixer until smooth.
Add milk and extract.
Beat until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip and food coloring.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Smooth with spatula. Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped topping and a cherry before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cookie pie crust
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg yolk; add flour.
Work with hands until blended.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges brown; cool thoroughly.
Fill with your favorite Jell-O pie mix.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Whip cottage cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add dry Jell-O. Fold in pineapple and oranges.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream the powdered sugar and cream cheese. Spread about 1/4-inch in crust. Spread pineapple, bananas and 1/4 cup nuts. Mix remaining mixture of powdered sugar
with Cool Whip. Spread over top. Top with cherries and remaining nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray a pan (9 x 13-inch) with vegetable spray.
Spread rice in sprayed pan.
Layer chicken over rice; sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
(Can also add 1 can cream of mushroom soup.)

title: muffin cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat until fluffy.
Mix baking powder with salt until there are no lumps and add flour.
Alternately beat in dry ingredients and milk.
Add vanilla.
Half fill buttered muffin pans or paper baking cups placed in muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for about 11 minutes on middle shelf of oven.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water.
Remove from heat; stir into stuffing. Add egg and sausage.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour, then shape into small balls.

Cut bacon strips into thirds, crosswise; wrap one piece around dressing mixture and fasten with toothpick. Place on rack in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown and crisp, turning at 1/2 point.
Drain on paper towel. Serve hot.
May be made ahead of time.

title: poppy seed rolls
directions: Separate dough and loosely tie each piece of dough into a knot, tucking in ends.
Arrange rolls 1 inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked ham
directions: Use enough juice to make a paste with other ingredients. Spread over ham.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes per pound.

title: barbecue beef short ribs
directions: Fill large stockpot with water and bring to boil. Add ribs, garlic and bay leaf. Cover. Parboil for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until fork-tender. In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients. Pour in 1 cup of rib water mixture. Cook over medium heat; stir occasionally for approximately 15 minutes or until sauce has thickened and is heated through. Add ribs to pot, turning with tong to coat well. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to grill meat side down and cook 8 to 10 minutes on each side; take care not to burn.

title: one day pickles
directions: Prepare a pickling mixture by adding to each cup of vinegar you desire to use, 1 tablespoon each of fine salt and pulverized table mustard.
Put this mixture into a glass fruit jar or jars, or a stone crock.
Select medium size cucumbers; wash and dry them thoroughly, as the secret of this process lies in their being absolutely dry when dropped into the mixture.
Put in a sufficient quantity to be well covered; cover jar tightly.
They are ready for use the following day.
By replenishing cucumbers as pickles are used, a progressive supply is assured at any time during the summer.

title: grandma's hello dolly's
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients; press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: three minute dessert
directions: Drain fruit well.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir gently. Refrigerate and serve.

title: tortilla chips
directions: Using a cookie cutter or kitchen shears, cut 3 (2-inch) rounds from each tortilla.
Combine lime juice and water in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine salt and remaining ingredients.
Dip tortillas in lime juice mixture; drain on paper towels.
Arrange tortillas in a single layer on an ungreased baking sheet; sprinkle evenly with salt mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until chips are crisp.
Cool; store in airtight containers.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, beaten egg, horseradish, salt, ketchup, milk and seasoning salt.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: sexy shrimp
directions: Prepare pasta as package directs.
Meanwhile, in a 10-inch skillet, heat oil over medium flame and cook sugar snaps, about 3 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Toss cooked pasta with sugar snaps, cherry tomatoes and Italian dressing to mix well and set aside.

title: fried rice
directions: In a skillet, heat oil, then add onions and stir.
Next, add rice and season mix, still stirring, add soy sauce and heat through.
Add eggs and mushrooms, cooking until eggs are done. Then add meat, heating through.
More soy sauce can be added when finished cooking.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits and salt to taste.
Add margarine and cheese, stirring until melted.
Then add eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Milk may be added if more fluid is needed.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 325°.

title: party biscuits *
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients together; add dissolved yeast and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out about 1/4 inch thick, cut with 1 1/2-inch cutter (or smaller).
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Split and stuff with fried ham or sausage. Makes 35 biscuits.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking pan.
Mix rice, water, celery soup and mushroom soup, then pour over chicken.
Sprinkle 1 package Lipton dry onion soup on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours between 300° to 325°.
No salt.
No peek.

title: old fruit cake
directions: Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together margarine and Crisco; add sugar and vanilla and cream thoroughly.
Add egg and cream until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.
If you prefer a soft cookie, use whipped margarine instead of Crisco and margarine.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze with ice cream freezer.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Just dump it all in and beat as you would any cake.
Use a Bundt pan.
You might need to grease and flour one if it is not Teflon.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Wait 15 minutes and turn out.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding into pineapple chunks and juice; add other ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and mix.
Add pineapple preserves, cherries and nuts last.
Bake 250° until done. At least 2 hours.

title: cathy's no sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: coconut-almond candy bars
directions: Butter a 12 x 9-inch piece of foil; set aside.
In a small bowl combine powdered sugar, softened cream cheese and vanilla. Stir in coconut.
Turn onto buttered foil.
Pat into a 10 x 5-inch rectangle.
Cut mixture into 2 x 1-inch rectangles.
Press 2 whole almonds into the top of each rectangle.

title: southwestern alaska cod chowder
directions: Saute bacon in large saucepan over medium high heat until crisp.
Stir in onions, garlic, cumin and pepper flakes.
Saute 5 minutes or until onions are soft.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly then gradually whisk in chicken broth.
Stir in tomatoes, wine, peppers, and sweet potato. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish and corn; simmer 2 - 3 minutes or until fish flakes.
Season with lime juice and pepper.

title: peanut butter pie(light)
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl with mixer and pour in crust; chill.

title: orange julius
directions: Place ice cubes in blender.
Blend until cracked.
Add sugar, vanilla, milk, water and orange juice.
Blend all until slushy!

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and cheese spreads, mixing until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup onions.
Chill.
Shape into ball; roll in remaining onions.
Serve with crackers.

title: party salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
When cool, add rest of ingredients. Mold and chill.

title: stromboli
directions: Place dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dough should be oblong.
Arrange ham and salami down the center of dough. Sprinkle half of basil and oregano over meat.
Arrange Provolone over herbs.
Top with Mozzarella, then remainder of herbs.
Fold sides to center; pinch together.
Brush top with butter; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Invert and brush with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: quick and easy goulash
directions: In large skillet, brown ground chuck with salt, pepper and onion; drain.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms to ground chuck mixture.
Bring to simmer.
Add corn and macaroni.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir cheese into mixture until melted.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions in 9 x 13 dish. While cake is cooking and nearly done, melt butter over low heat in saucepan.
Add cocoa, sugar and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Poke holes all in cake while it is hot and pour heated mixture over cake.

title: orange almond lettuce salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, pepper and almond extract.
Place almonds and 2 tablespoons sugar in small frypan.
Stir over low heat, stirring until sugar is melted, adhering to almonds.
Pour onto plate to cool, break into pieces.
Add nuts and oranges (drained) to vegetables.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onion
and
salt.
Let
stand
hour. Combine vinegar, sugar, pepper, mustard and celery seed. Bring to a boil. Add squash
and onion.
Bring to a good boil.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: garlic loaf
directions: Cut each biscuit in half.
Mix garlic, parsley and margarine. Dip biscuits in mixture and place in 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: green beans in onion and garlic sauce
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water using a large saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the beans and simmer until nearly all the liquid has evaporated, turning them constantly.
Heat the oil and butter in a pan.
Add the garlic and the spring onions (shallots or scallions).
Stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add the beans and toss in the fat until well coated.
Sprinkle with the soy sauce, sugar and sherry.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Serve hot.

title: peach-pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium size bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except beans.
Stir beans into mixture in baking dish.
Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: easy pineapple angel food
directions: Mix. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Turn oven off and leave oven door ajar 10 minutes.
Remove cake and let cool.

title: pear honey
directions: Quarter pears, core and peel.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
Drain pears, mash with potato masher, add lemon juice, grated lemon rind and sugar.
One quarter teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 nutmeg may be added, if desired.
Cook quickly until the consistency of jam.
Stir carefully to avoid scorching. Pour into sterilized jars and seal with paraffin.
Makes 4 to 6 small jars.

title: creamy strawberry parfait
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients; stir well and set aside. Combine sour cream and whipped topping.
Stir well; set aside. Spoon 1/4 cup of frozen yogurt into six 8-ounce parfait glasses. Top with 1/2 cup strawberry mixture and 1 tablespoon of sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Mix
the
shortening, orange rind, eggs, juice and milk until smooth.
Add
dry ingredients (not oranges).
Mix well. Pour into a
greased
and
floured
13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange oranges on top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put honey, peanut butter, egg and butter in a bowl and mix well with an electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add flour and baking powder and mix with a spoon.
Drop mixture by the spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/3 can of onion rings. Spoon into baking dish and top with remaining onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian seasoning mix
directions: Mix together very well and store in airtight container.
Use on dry roasted and barbecued meats, hamburgers and pot roast. Great in chili, soups, stews and spaghetti sauce.
Excellent in bean dishes and stir-fry.
For a stronger spice mix, use 1 1/2 cups Hawaiian salt.

title: seedless blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat juice, vanilla, and sugar until hot. In small bowl, mix cornstarch in water and stir until smooth. Add to hot juice and cook until thick. Remove from heat and prepare sweet dough.

title: ice tea concentrate
directions: Boil water.
Add tea bags.
Let stand 6 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar while tea is hot.
Put tea concentrate in a quart jar.
Add enough water to make 1 quart.
This 1 quart of concentrate will make 4 quarts of ice tea by adding water and ice.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in soups, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Cook lima beans 15 minutes.
Add all ingredients except cheese to beans.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes. About 5 minutes before taking from oven, add cheese and leave in oven long enough to melt.

title: tourtiere
directions: In a saucepan combine pork, water, onions and garlic.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Drain fat.

title: green punch
directions: Add sugar and water.
Cook until it becomes syrup.
Combine jello and 2 cups hot water; dissolve as making jello.
Add to syrup.
Add lemon juice, almond extract, ginger ale and pineapple.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie with caramel pecan sauce
directions: Blend cookies, butter and sugar.
Press into 9-inch pie pan. Refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.
In large bowl, combine ice cream and cinnamon.
Spoon into chilled crust and freeze.
Combine brown sugar, ginger, cloves and pumpkin.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over ice cream in crust.
Freeze 3 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Top with sauce.
(Cook caramel topping and pecans over medium heat, stir constantly.)

title: "catfish fried" chicken
directions: Marinate chicken pieces in buttermilk about 2 hours.
Mix flour, cornmeal and spices in a bowl.
Dredge marinated chicken and fry in oil or a combination of oil and butter or margarine.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine Hershey's chocolate syrup and Eagle Brand milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool while making rest of cake.

title: sweet roll dough(very good for caramel or cinnamon rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In large bowl, combine milk, sugar, salt and oleo.
Stir until oleo is melted. Add yeast mixture.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour.
Mix well; add remaining flour until you get a soft dough.
Knead very well and place in a greased bowl.
Let rise until double; punch down and let rise a second time.
Make into rolls.
Let rise and bake.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts.
Spread in an 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: christmas salad(or no lettuce salad)
directions: Cut or chop all vegetables.
Combine all vegetables in bowl. Pour Italian dressing over salad and let set overnight in refrigerator.
You can use any fresh vegetables in this salad.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cut up bacon and fry in bottom of large pot.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until potatoes are soft, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamy mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls the size of English walnuts.
Roll balls into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, Rice Krispies and powdered sugar.
Form into tiny balls and freeze for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate in the microwave for 2 minutes or until melted.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper. Cool.
Makes approximately 60 balls.

title: two-handed oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugars, peanut butter, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Drop dough from an ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup-measure several inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.

title: corn gems
directions: Scald milk and add to margarine, sugar, salt and cornmeal. Allow to cool and melt margarine.
Stir in yeast.
Add 2 cups of flour.
Turn onto floured board and knead.
Allow to rest 10 minutes.
Roll into 16 inch diameter or larger.
Cut in 24 wedges. Roll, start at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Raise. Grease with margarine and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, water and vinegar.
Cook to hard boil stage (250°).
Remove from heat; wipe crystals off pan.
Add soda; stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour over corn, mixing well and shape into 2 1/2-inch balls.
Makes 10 balls.

title: double chocolate crumb bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, nuts and cocoa to creamed mixture.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on top.
Bake 3 minutes more; cool.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into large loaf pan.
Top with topping.

title: chili cocktail pie
directions: Layer chilies over bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Grate cheese over chilies.
Beat eggs and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it appears firm when pan is shaken. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: 5-minute pineapple cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Combine sugar, vanilla and eggs in large mixer bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed. At low speed, add flour, soda, salt and pineapple and beat 1 minute. Pour into pan; sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar, coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Just before cake is done, prepare sauce. Pour over warm cake. Cool before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add water to make 1 gallon.

title: one hour buttermilk rolls *(like angel biscuits)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, sugar, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water, add buttermilk and stir into flour mixture.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead lightly as when preparing biscuits.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise for one hour. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 24 to 28 rolls.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach by directions; drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape spinach mixture into 3/4-inch balls and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 80 balls.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together as given.
Use jello dry.
Do not dilute with water.
Chill and serve.

title: scandanavian bean salad
directions: Mix above ingredients in large bowl. Add dressing.

title: savory pepper steak (west)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper and toss meat in mixture. Heat fat over high heat.
Cook beef about four minutes or until browned. Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients. Simmer 45-60 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: chocolate coffee pie
directions: Prepare graham crust.
Fold chocolate, coffee and water into Cool Whip and pour into the graham crust.
Place in freezer to chill and can be served directly from freezer to table.

title: easy pecan caramels
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over bottom.
Mix brown sugar and corn syrup in a 2-quart glass measure.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Grease and flour pan first.
Beat eggs with fork in large bowl. Add dry cake mix, vanilla and pie filling.
Stir until blended by hand.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Frost while warm.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter, sugar and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and molasses.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: In a large, nonreactive bowl, combine all ingredients, except shrimp.
Whisk together.
Fill a large kettle 3/4 full of water; bring to a boil over high heat.
Add shrimp; cook until opaque in the center, or for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain; add to the marinade, stirring to coat.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir cornmeal into water.
Add butter and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: swiss creamed peas
directions: In a saucepan, cook peas according to directions.
In a medium saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend in the flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add cream and lemon peel.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.
Drain peas and add to sauce.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in eggs, pumpkin pie spice, salt and milk.
Fold in grated sweet potatoes.
Pour into a buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish and bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: layered green salad
directions: Lettuce in bottom of pan or dish.
Layer of green pepper, layer of onions.
Layer of water chestnuts.
Put peas on top.
Put chopped bacon on peas.
Mix sugar, lemon juice and dash of garlic salt with mayonnaise.
Spread on top and then put cheese on top of mayonnaise.

title: zesty shrimp
directions: Saute the shrimp until just barely done.
Add dressing mix and enough butter to make a sauce.	Keep heat on very low flame to combine flavors.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: chinese cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumber.
Cut into very thin slices.
Sprinkle salt and let stand for at least 20 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.

title: depression casserole
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Stir in ketchup, water, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Place frankfurters in a 1-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over it.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over toast or rice.

title: spicy sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, pour off fat.
Reduce heat; add pepper, onion, raw macaroni, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for 10 minutes more. Spoon into buttered 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: jellied waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add 3/4 cup of cold water and chill until thickens.
Pour in mold until thick; top with cream.

title: dunkin' franks
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients (except hot dogs).
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces.
Add hot dogs to sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Use toothpicks for dunking.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Crush gingersnaps.
In a large bowl, combine crumbs, milk and eggs.
Add chuck, pork, onions, salt, pepper and allspice; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into meatballs 1 inch in diameter.
Moist hands work well.
In a large skillet, melt butter and saute meatballs until brown all over; do not crowd.
Remove to a 2-quart casserole as they are finished.
Pour off drippings; reserve 1/4 cup in pan.
Heat drippings.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute and put in beef bouillon.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 25 appetizer servings.
Can be served with rice.
Delicious!

title: blue bandana bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Mash bananas.
Stir in. Drain blueberries and fold in.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked stuffed hard clams
directions: Drain and chop clams.
Melt margarine or butter in pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
If mixture is too dry, moisten with water. Fill 1/2 clam shells or any ovenproof dishes with clam mixture. Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fish fry(like long john silver's)
directions: Thaw fish.
Prepare Sweet-Sour Sauce (below).
Separate fillets.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Heat oil in a Fry Daddy. Mix flour, water, baking powder and salt.
Using tongs, coat fillets with batter.
Fry fish in hot oil until golden.
Drain well and serve with Sweet-Sour Sauce.

title: barbecued ham sandwiches
directions: Mix and heat first 4 ingredients.
Add to chipped ham.
Heat well.
Serve on warm buns.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Blend food coloring and cocoa together.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in cocoa mixture. Add flour, salt and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Fold in vanilla.
At the same time, add vinegar and soda.
Fold in.
Will tend to foam. Pour into two 9-inch pans or three 8-inch pans. Be sure to line pans with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Refrigerate and serve.
Makes 2 cups plus.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and roll into small balls.
Them melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip all balls into chocolate, making them look like buckeyes.
Set on wax paper.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and pour all wet ingredients into it.
Stir only until moistened.
Stir in cheese.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda; stir well and set aside. Combine Coke, butter and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir into flour mixture. Stir in buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: bubble recipe
directions: Combine ingredients and shake.
Let set 4 hours, stored covered in refrigerator.
Allow to warm before using.
Bubbles best on humid, cloudy days.
Have fun.

title: date balls
directions: Combine chopped dates, margarine and sugar.
Cook until mushy and sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Let cool.
Roll into small balls.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 10.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Peel peaches; add sugar and let stand overnight.
Then add vinegar and spices (tied in cheesecloth) and cook until peaches are done.
Lift out and place in jars.
Let juice boil until thick, then pour over peaches and seal.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix with pudding in a large bowl and form a well in the center.
Mix sour cream, water, oil and eggs.
Pour into the well and combine both mixtures, beating well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour in a greased and floured funnel cake pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper nuts
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Dough will be very stiff. On waxed paper, shape into rolls 1-inch in diameter.
Chill overnight; slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Mix beans, Bisquick and water together and pack down gently in the bottom of a small ungreased baking pan. Brown ground beef and drain. Layer beef, taco sauce and cheese on top of Bisquick mixture, ending with a final topping of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes to firm.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in bowl until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix milk, flour and sugar together.
Mix lemon, eggs and salt together.
Combine both mixtures.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Fruit ferments 6 weeks.

title: orange-peach pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cornstarch, salt and water until smooth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir until thickened. Stir in Splenda and gelatin. Cool. Fold in peaches. Pour into the pie crust. Refrigerate for 2 hours or until serving. Garnish with whipped topping (optional).

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil.
Simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto greased wax paper.

title: red cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage quite fine.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Add cabbage, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Cook slowly until done. Season to taste with additional salt, sugar, vinegar, jelly or fruit juice.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend flour and 3/4 c. plus 2 Tbsp sugar and set aside.
Measure egg whites, cream of tartar and salt into a large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed until foamy.
Add 3/4 c sugar, 2 Tbsp at a time, beating on high speed until the meringue holds stiff, glossy peaks.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks until very thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes.
Fold flavorings into the meringue.
Then sprinkle the flour, sugar mixture, 1/4 at a time, over the meringue folding in carefully just until the flour, sugar mixture disappears.
Pour half the batter into another bowl.
Gently fold in egg yolks.
Spoon the yellow and white batters alternately into an ungreased tube pan 10 x4 inches. Gently cut through the batters to make a swirling effect.
Bake at lowest rack in oven 40 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Immediately invert tube pan on a catsup bottle and let hang until cake is completely cool at least 2 hours.
Spread the cake with Lemon glaze.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, juice, egg and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Refrigerate until cold.
Fold in Cool Whip and the cooled dressing together.
Add fruits and nuts.
Drizzle caramel toping on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Put in glass bowl. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mel's chili
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, water and garlic.
Simmer till thick - about 2 hours.
Add chili beans, seasoning, salt & pepper.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Top with grated cheese.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine kraut, celery, bell pepper, onion and pimento.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour dressing over kraut mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours, stirring once or twice.

title: hamburger plantation
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Prepare egg noodles according to package directions.
Add ground beef and onion mixture to corn, soup, pimento and cream cheese until bubbly, stirring to blend evenly.
Add egg noodles to meat mixture and simmer approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with hot, crusty bread and a green salad.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in a pan of water with bouillon cubes.
Boil until you get a rich broth.
Add more water as needed.
Add noodles. When done, add mushrooms and carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape, wash and slice carrots.
