Cook until tender (do not overcook).
Drain well.
Chop onion and green pepper (coarsely). In a large bowl, add onion, green pepper and cooked carrots.
Mix together:
tomato soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Pour the tomato soup mixture over carrots, etc.
Cover tightly and chill several hours or overnight.
Great for outings!

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Put butter and oil in shallow baking pan.
Heat in oven.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika; coat chicken with this.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Dip floured chicken in egg mixture; roll in bread crumbs.
Place in oiled pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: jumbles(sugar cookies)
directions: Combine ingredients; drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: raw apple nut cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Mix well the remaining ingredients. Add flour mixture a little at a time.
Pour into angel food cake pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and peanut butter.
Add white and brown sugars.
Stir in egg, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Place dough, a teaspoon at a time, onto cookie sheet, pressing each dab flat with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool a minute or two before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen. Contains approximately 50 calories per serving.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Peel and shred.
Combine cheese and butter over low heat and stir.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Put into medium-size casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fried won tons
directions: Filling:
Add water, cornstarch, salt and sesame oil to meat. Mix thoroughly until the meat is completely blended and smooth.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Dump in eggs and mash all together.
Add onion, pickle relish, celery seed, mustard and enough mayonnaise to make it creamy.
Mash.
Add vinegar and mash again.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Saute onion and peppers in butter.
Stir in white sauce or soup mixture, mushrooms and basil.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: mom's coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to directions, adding 1 teaspoon of coconut flavoring. Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans. Cool layers and split. Mix by hand sugar, Cool Whip, 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring, sour cream and 7 ounces dry coconut. Spread between layers and ice remaining cake. Sprinkle with frozen coconut.

title: mom stephen's wild rice and crab salad
directions: In saucepan, combine wild rice, salt and 1 1/2 cups water. Simmer, covered, 35 to 45 minutes, until rice is tender.
Drain, if necessary.
Let rice cool 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Cover; top with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: onion soup
directions: In heavy pan, saute the onions in butter, stirring occasionally, until golden.
Sprinkle with flour and stir for a few minutes to cook the flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.
Toast the bread in oven and place them in a large ovenproof soup tureen or individual bowls.
Sprinkle toast with Parmesan cheese.
Ladle soup in bowls on top of bread and top with grated cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbling and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add well sifted flour, salt and soda.
Mix well, then add chopped nuts, fresh apples and vanilla by hand.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Clean the vegetables and let stand in cold water 10 minutes. Cut vegetables in small pieces.
Mix and cream dressing mixture together.
Pour over vegetables and crumble in bacon.
Mix well. Chill and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Serve.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch Bundt cake pan.
Cream the butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add the egg yolks and beat well.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Stir the jam into sour cream.
Add the dry mixture to the creamed mixture, alternating with the sour cream.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, then fold into the batter.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add them alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan; bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch crescents
directions: Prepare pudding mix in milk until thick.
Stir in oleo.
Cool until warm.
Add eggs, salt and yeast that was softened in water. Gradually add flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Then divide in thirds.
Roll each into 15-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Place filling on each and roll to center.
Put on greased sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: layer bars
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: high protein peanut butter balls
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Makes balls and flatten.
Put in container; keep refrigerated. Great snacks and energy builder-uppers.

title: five layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Press graham crumbs into margarine.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 1 minute. Sprinkle on chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Cook in microwave on High for approximately 6 to 8 minutes, or until bubbling all over surface.
Cool; cut in 1-inch bars.
Do not refrigerate.
You can freeze these cookies.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour half in dish and let congeal.
Spread with 1 cup sour cream.
Pour rest of mixture on top and let congeal.

title: tightwad baked beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight in cold water.
In the morning pour off the soaking water and parboil beans with baking soda in fresh water until the skins are cracked when blown upon.
Cut onion in quarters and put in the bottom of a beanpot or a large casserole dish.
Add parboiled beans and put cut up bacon on top of the beans. Mix brown sugar, molasses, dry mustard and salt with a pint of water.
If needed, add more boiling water while baking.
Bake at 300° for about 6
hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan.
Spoon undrained pineapple over and spread.
Add pie filling and spread.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over.
Sprinkle pecans; spread pats of butter over. Bake 48 to 53 minutes.

title: shrimp dip(low-fat recipe)
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill. Makes 3 cups.
Twelve 1/4 cup servings.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat oven at 400°, lightly grease a 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle broccoli, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in medium size bowl with electric mixer until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 35 minutes or until top is golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any remaining quiche.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then mix rest of ingredients and pour over the others.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and flour.
Beat well.
Add chips.
Sift flour and soda together and stir into the creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar
and butter; add apples after soda has been added. Add flavoring to flour and sift twice.
Flour nuts and raisins and
fold
into
batter.
Add
well
beaten eggs last. Bake in greased and floured tube pan in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: gingered baked fruit
directions: Get the stuff for crust and them make it.
Put "basketti" sauce on it.
Put cheese on it.
Put mushrooms and more cheese on it.
Cook your pizza.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar.
Add meal and flour.
Mix and then add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 2 unbaked pie crusts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry mixture to egg mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Use large pan (9 x 14 x 1 1/2-inches).

title: layered pork chop casserole
directions: In
a
large
casserole
dish,
pour 1/3 can of soup, 4 chops and 1/2 of the following:
onions, carrots and potatoes. Season with
salt
and
pepper.
Layer
again, beginning with soup.
Add the last of the soup and cabbage quarters.
Cover. Bake at 325°. Cook 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove from bones. Place in large baking dish.
Cover with chicken.
Combine soup, sherry and egg yolks.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour warm water into a large bowl (first rinse in real hot water).
If possible, check temperature with thermometer.
The water should be warm, not hot (test on under part of wrist). Sprinkle yeast over water.
Add sugar and salt; stir to dissolve completely.
Add egg, soft butter and 3 cups of flour with wooden spoon or electric mixer at medium speed; beat very hard 2 minutes or until smooth.
Gradually add 1 cup of flour, beating hard after each addition.
Using hands, work remaining 2 cups flour into the dough, working dough with hands until smooth and elastic.
Brush top of the dough with melted butter; cover with a double thickness of a damp towel.
Let rise in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down dough and refrigerate, if not cooking at the time.
It can be kept 1 or 3 days and then cooked.

title: quick cheese and pepper bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 loaf pan. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cheese, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and pepper; mix well.
In small bowl combine buttermilk, margarine and eggs; blend well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; remove.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Wrap; store in refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Cook on medium about 20 minutes, then simmer about 2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna and set aside.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add sauce, mushrooms, green pepper and onion.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: raw potato pancakes
directions: Mix well.
Fry in Crisco and butter.
Serve with applesauce.

title: glenn's lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly. Add next 6 ingredients to meat. Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles until tender. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half of the cheese mixture over the noodles.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: man on the moon cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with Lunar Topping.
Cool before cutting.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saut pan. Brown pork chops, then remove. Add bell pepper and onion; saut. Take off heat and add soups and rice. Stir. Lay pork chops on top and cover. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend first three ingredients together.
Shape into two balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate a day or so before using.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a large sauce pan; add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add butter.
Place over high heat and bring to a boil.
Boil until smooth, about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool completely.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients (chicken, celery, lemon juice, salt, onion, mayonnaise and nuts).
Pour into casserole dish and top with chips and grated cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear cake into pieces and stir in 1 large container Cool Whip. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and the other container of Cool Whip and spread onto first layer.
Mix glaze and strawberries together and spread over second layer.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Scald milk and cool slightly.
Add shortening, salt and brown sugar and stir.
When lukewarm, add egg and yeast, which has been dissolved in the 1/2 cup warm water.
Add whole wheat flour and white flour and mix until all flour is moistened.
Let dough rest 5 minutes.
Knead bread for 10 minutes.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Form into 2 loaves or dinner rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lillie jessup's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco, sugar and flavorings.
Add sour cream.
Sift flour 3 times with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk, beating all this time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each addition.
Bake at 325°.
Test for doneness after 1 hour and 15 minutes, but it may take as long as 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Sift flour, salt, soda and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Add cranberry mixture and combine slightly.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: dill oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add dry dressing mix, dill and garlic powder.
Stir.
Add oyster crackers and stir to mix thoroughly.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Layer carrots, croutons, and cheese.
Saute onions and garlic in margarine.
Add flour to the pan and stir well.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Pour over the carrots.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown on the top.

title: toasted clam sandwiches
directions: Most Sea Islanders historically use a bateau, a net and a pair of oars
all
of
which
they
made themselves to catch enough seafoods for
their
families
to
eat
and
to sell at nearby cities.
A	variety
of fishes were in abundance in the creeks around the Islands:
croakers, poggies and bass.

title: grandma's shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until browned, approx. 20 minutes. AT our house we serve this with chicken and gravy for the meal
then with strawberries and ice cream for dessert.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package in 13 x 9 inch pan. While still warm, punch holes in top of cake with handle of wooden spoon.

Mix Eagle Brand milk, 1/2 can cream of coconut. Pour over cake and refrigerate to cool. Combine Cool Whip and other 1/2 can of cream of coconut and spread on top of cooled cake. Top with coconut. Needs to be kept refrigerated. Is better if made at least one day ahead.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Pan size: 9 x 13-inches.
Baking time: 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken divan
directions: Slice chicken into small pieces.
Spray baking dish with Pam. Pour bag of broccoli into pan.
Add chicken.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream and add to chicken and broccoli. Combine crackers and margarine.
Crumble together and top chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: gloria's sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar, flour, salt, water and vanilla. Beat eggs, adding the baking powder a little at a time while beating.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of batter comes out clean.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, yogurt, honey and ginger; beat until creamy.
Fold in pineapple.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion together with oleo.
Mix altogether. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
In small bowl, soak bread in milk. In large bowl, combine onion, bread and remaining ingredients. Mix with hands until thoroughly combined.
Shape into a loaf and place in loaf pan (lightly greased).
Bake 1 hour.

title: diabetic cupcakes
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft. Drain off water. Mix applesauce, eggs and sweetener. Add oil. Mix well. Add baking soda and flour. Add remaining ingredients and stir in raisins. Bake cake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Bring sugar, water, shortening and raisins to a boil.
Let cool a little. Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir to mix. Add fruit cake mix and chopped nuts. Grease a loaf pan. Cut waxed or brown paper to fit bottom of pan and grease again.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Remove from pan and remove paper. Glaze with honey and decorate with cherries or nuts.

title: burritos
directions: Add 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt to mashed beans, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon dry onions.
Cook hamburger and add taco seasonings.
Mix beans, meat and shredded cheese.
Butter 1 side of tortillas; fill with 1 to 2 tablespoons filling.
Roll up and place margarine side out in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake at 500° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Roll in plastic wrap and freeze.
Microwave for 2 minutes.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inch) in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Let meat loaf stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: rice green chilies cheese bake
directions: Thinly slice zucchini and tomato.
Chop chilies, pepper and onion.
Grate cheese.
Cook rice.
Cook zucchini in small amount of water until crisp-tender.

title: granola cereal
directions: Heat the oil and honey in the microwave for about 1 minute so it pours easily.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir after 10 minutes.
When thoroughly cooled, package in airtight bag.

title: pear nut bread
directions: Coarsely grate pears to make 2 cups.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, lemon peel, vanilla and grated pears.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to pear mixture, mixing until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 3 medium greased loaf pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until done.

title: mrs. miller's cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until just beginning to brown slightly.
Do not overcook.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: pork chop n' potato bake
directions: Brown chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 4 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Place all ingredients except topping in a blender container.
Blend on high speed, stopping blender occasionally to stir, until smooth, about 3 minutes (or beat in a large bowl on high speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes).
Pour into a plate; bake just until puffed and center is dry, about 30 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage.
Add mushrooms, celery, onions and bell pepper; add water and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Mix in 3 cups corn bread and bake until crisp in 350° oven.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Add crushed peppermint and nuts.
Pour over popcorn and put in a buttered tube pan.
Chill. Cut.
Serve.

title: carrot soup
directions: Heat butter or oil in cooker.
Saute leeks for 2 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery, stock, tarragon, salt and pepper. Bring ingredients to boil.
Cover and cook over medium heat until carrots are very soft (about 20 minutes).
In blender or food mill, puree soup in batches.
Return soup to cooker to reheat before serving.
Garnish with watercress or tarragon (or parsley). Serves 6.

title: pickled onions and peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in jar; cover and let stand at room temperature 3 to 4 days.
Refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook and stir constantly until makes a hard ball in water. Take off heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda; stir well.
Pour over corn.

title: zucchini with peanuts
directions: Steam the zucchini for about 2 to 3 minutes, then put it in a skillet with the butter and fry.
When the zucchini is soft, put in the soy sauce and the lemon stuff and then the peanuts.
It's really good with rice.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Blend in mixer: sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings, then flour and milk alternately. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: caramel squares
directions: Combine brown sugar and butter in pan over low heat (after butter is melted, add sugar).
Take pan off of heat and add flour, salt, vanilla, eggs and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour pie filling.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Sprinkle brown sugar and mix well.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apples and spread evenly.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: jack daniel's chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Separate the eggs.
Add yolks to and blend with chocolate.
(Be sure the yolks are the same temperature as the chocolate.)

title: wonder frosting
directions: Blend flour and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles.
Cool.
Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in flour mixture in portions until soft and fluffy.

title: chocolate chip brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) with waxed paper, grease.
Heat butter and 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until melted.
Stir remaining ingredients (except frosting) into melted chocolate. Spread evenly into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Invert on board.
Remove wax paper.
Cool completely.

title: four layer chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients in pan for this layer. Mash over bottom and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: rum balls
directions: Grind nuts, vanilla wafers and chocolate chips together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: tex-mex
directions: Spread bean dip on large platter.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; layer on top of bean dip.
Add tomatoes, olives, green onions and cheese on top.
Use the round tostado chips in box (Old El Paso).
They don't break as much.
Everyone will love this!

title: cheese pastry shell
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle milk, one tablespoon at a time, evenly over surface.
Stir with fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape into a ball. Chill 30 minutes.

title: north carolina pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after every addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk, 1/3 at a time. Add flavorings.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°, or until done.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: In a medium bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed, combine Port wine cheese, cream cheese, onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl; place in freezer 5 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Freeze with milk to line (about 1/2 gallon) in ice cream freezer.

title: chocolate pancakes
directions: Mix cornmeal,
pancake mix, sugar and cocoa.
Beat egg. Add egg
and
milk
to dry ingredients.
Mix.
Cook in 12-inch Dutch oven with
lid
off, until edges are dry.
Turn and cook for 2 minutes on other side.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend first three ingredients together well.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture and blend well.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until done in a greased and floured pan.

title: egg casserole(brunch)
directions: Hard-cook eggs; peel, slice and set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
Melt margarine; add flour, milk and half and half to make cream sauce.
Add basil, thyme, marjoram and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Grease 9 x 6-inch baking dish.
Layer half the eggs, half the bacon and half the cheese; repeat.
Melt remaining margarine.
Add bread crumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Let set 8 hours or overnight. Bake in 350° oven until brown on top, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bennett's homemade tortillas
directions: Combine flour and baking soda, then add salt and pepper. Combine shortening into mixture, using a fork or pastry knife, until mixture is crumbly, then slowly add boiling water.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Cover and let it rest for 15 minutes, until shiny.

title: polish potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cool; slice.
Cook bacon; reserve grease. Crumble in potatoes.
Add pickle, salt and pepper.
Cut onion in small pieces.
Heat bacon grease; add flour, sugar and vinegar. Make a roux.
Add to potatoes and mix well.
If too dry, add more warm water.
Tastes better warm and good for picnics.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cook 1 box of vanilla and 1 box of chocolate pudding according to the directions on the box.
Line the bottom and the sides of a loaf pan with graham crackers.
Then layer sliced bananas or peaches followed by vanilla pudding, followed by a layer of graham crackers.
Then layer bananas or peaches followed by chocolate pudding and then bananas or peaches.
Top with crushed graham crackers.
Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and peanut butter until very smooth. Add confectioners sugar and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell (graham cracker or cooled pastry).
Chill and spread Cool Whip on top.
Grated chocolate pieces on top are very good.

title: rice o'brien
directions: In 2-quart baking dish, combine rice, chopped onion, salt, poultry seasoning, soy sauce, chopped pepper and chicken broth. Cover; bake at 375° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender and bubbly.

title: napoli casserole
directions: Make white sauce (first 4 ingredients) and add 1/2 cup of cheese.
Cut sausage into small pieces.
Brown in skillet and drain grease.
Add zucchini and onions; cook until clear.
Stir in sauce, noodles and tomatoes.
Pour into casserole dish (2-quart); top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large bowl.
Set aside.
Put remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over the ingredients in large bowl.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Scald sour cream; stir in butter, sugar and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water; mix together.
Add eggs and flour. Refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough in 3 equal portions.
Roll each in a circle about 9 to 10-inches in diameter.
Cut in pie wedges.
Roll up to make crescent rolls.
Dip in margarine and place on well-buttered pan.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break up angel food cake in small pieces and place in a large deep bowl (punch bowl works well).
Next mix instant pudding according to package directions.
Pour pudding over cake.
Next, spread the cherry pie filling.
Seal with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans and decorate with drained red or green cherries, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of casserole dish with green beans next.
Put Swiss cheese over chicken and green beans.
Pour soup over all.
Top casserole with stuffing mix and bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing according to package directions; set aside.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms soft ball when tested in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Pour in greased pan and put in cool place to harden.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two loaf pans and line bottoms with waxed paper.
Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Nuts or raisins may be added if desired.

title: pecan tarts(double the recipe for crust and filling.)
directions: Make little balls; press into ungreased tart cups.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grandma's overnight bread
directions: About 6:00 P.M., make bread dough.
Combine water, yeast, shortening, eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Punch down.
Let rise 1 hour. Punch down and let rise again.

title: low fat chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Add chocolate syrup and oil.
Beat until smooth, then add flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly; add nuts or sprinkle on top for a crisp crust.

title: homemade coffee liqueur
directions: Mix coffee and sugar together.
Add boiling water slowly and stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla and stir.
Slowly pour and mix in Brandy or Vodka.
Store in capped bottles. Makes approximately 2-1/2 fifths. Best if aged for at least 1 month.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine and put in 4-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook pasta.
Mix cheeses, eggs and seasoning together.
Layer ingredients:
sauce, pasta, cheese mixture.
Use grated Parmesan cheese to sprinkle on top of cheese mixture between layers.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in a large baking dish.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: thirty minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Turn onto floured surface and knead.
Roll to half-inch thickness and cut into rolls.
Place into oiled pan, flipping to oil the tops.
Let rise for 30 minutes in warm place.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Brush with butter to make soft.
Makes 12 to 16 rolls.
Doubles easily.

title: festive fruit cookies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup oleo, brown sugar and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice, reserving remainder for frosting.
Stir until well blended.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to orange juice mixture, stirring until smooth.
Add nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Blend powdered sugar with oleo and reserved orange juice.
Frost hot cookies.

title: strawberry marshmallow salad
directions: Add fruit cocktail to jello and top with marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and lemon juice.
Pour into a greased 16 x 11 x 2-inch jelly roll pan.
Put 1 tablespoon filling into about 20 sections.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients, topping with Ranch dressing.

title: easy kuchen
directions: Melt butter in scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add egg, salt and sugar and dissolve yeast in milk.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise for 1 hour in warm place.
Punch down and let rise again.
Put into 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Let rise until doubled and bake 20 minutes in moderate oven at 375°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Clean and drain fresh fruit or canned fruit (seedless grapes are best). Combine in a large bowl with poppy seed and nuts.
Whip or blend at high
blending speed for 30 seconds all other ingredients to form a glaze. Cover fruit with glaze. Chill.

title: nelson special
directions: Decide what you have a taste for.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Crush the grahams and sprinkle evenly over margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients in layers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Chill.
When ready to serve, spoon onto a lettuce leaf and sprinkle with paprika.

title: fudge 2
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter. Don't stir.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes on high on the stove top.
Add nuts and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Spread into well-greased square dish. Chill until firm.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook together almonds, rice, pepper, mushrooms, onions and margarine until rice turns yellow, stirring often.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
DO NOT USE QUICK COOKING RICE.
Serves 6.

title: cheese stuffed peppers
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook peppers 3 minutes in boiling water to cover; drain.
Place in baking dish, cut side up.
Mix cheese and vegetables.
Fill peppers.
In small bowl, mix crumbs and butter until blended.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until vegetables are heated through and the crumbs are lightly browned.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream the butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.
For each cookie, drop 1/4 cup dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread into pumpkin shape using a thin metal spatula.
Add a bit more dough to form stem.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until cookies are firm and lightly browned.
Cool on rack.
Decorate using icing or peanut butter to affix assorted candies, nuts or raisins.
Makes 32 large cookies.

title: passover sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add a pinch of salt.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar to whites.
Beat until glossy and peaks form. Beat egg yolks in another bowl.
Gradually add the oil, sugar and juice.
Beat well about 5 minutes or so until light in color and thick.
Add rind.

title: texas barbecue(fow slow cooker)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over 2 1/2 to 3 pound roast in slow cooker.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on medium or low heat, until meat is tender.
Remove meat and allow to cool.
Slice thin, across the grain.
Skim off fat from sauce.
Heat sauce.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
Stir into sauce and stir until thickened.
Return meat to sauce.
Heat through, about 30 minutes. Serve on split hard rolls, hamburger rolls or sandwich rolls. Makes enough for a small crowd.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to buttermilk.
Stir well.
Add to flour mixture; mix until blended.
Knead for 1 minute, or until smooth. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut; place on ungreased biscuit pan. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Dough may be stored in bulk for 3 or 4 days in the refrigerator.
Yields 20 to 25.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, confectioners sugar and cream cheese. Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
May be frozen.
Cuts best when frozen.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: triple berry wake-up
directions: Spread some cream cheese on two slices of bread.
Top with strawberry slices, making a complete blanket over the cheese.
Top each with remaining bread.

title: coconut candy fudge
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Add softened margarine, coconut, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Press in greased or buttered pan so that the candy is about 1-inch thick.
Melt chocolate and pour over the candy when firm.
Cut into squares; tastes like Mounds candy bars.

title: cheese apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Soften cheese; butter the pan.
Cream cheese and margarine and gradually add flour and sugar alternately.
Pour apples in baking dish.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: quick molasses popcorn balls
directions: Keep corn warm in a 250° oven.
Mix molasses, sugar and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook without stirring 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour syrup slowly over popped corn, mixing with a buttered fork.
Continue to toss and mix to distribute syrup evenly.
When cool enough to handle but still quite warm, shape into cornballs.
Let stand in a warm place until cool and cornballs lose their stickiness.
Wrap in plastic film or put each ball in a small plastic bag; tie securely.
Store in covered container.

title: spicy coconut pears
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Combine 1/4 cup reserved liquid, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; stir until smooth.
Set aside.

Combine remaining 3/4 cup pear liquid, sugar, lemon juice and margarine in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Gradually stir in cornstarch mixture; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Arrange pears in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour sauce over pears; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squash-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender. Drain. Partially mash with a potato masher. Combine zucchini mixture, rice, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and eggs in a bowl. Stir gently. Spoon zucchini mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Preheat broiler. Broil 1 minute or until lightly browned. Yield: 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line bottom of baking pan with aluminum foil.
While oven is preheating, melt margarine in baking pan. Mix dry ingredients in bowl or plastic bag.
Coat chicken pieces by rolling or shaking in flour.
Place chicken pieces in melted margarine and turn over to have skin side down.
(Both sides will be covered with margarine.)
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken. Bake for 30 minutes more.

title: sis' frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring sugar
and
water
to
boil
in
small
saucepan. Reduce heat
and
simmer
until	syrupy,
minutes.
Cool. Combine remaining
ingredients
in large bowl.
Stir in cooled syrup. Spoon
into 18 foil-lined muffin cups and freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Remove and store in plastic bags. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 18 servings.	May be stored up to 1 month.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter; stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive and seal all edges. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. These may be made ahead and stored in refrigerator.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown over high heat in a nonstick pan, turning frequently. Transfer chicken to a baking dish. Set aside.
Combine tomato puree, mushrooms, onion flakes, celery, pimento, garlic, rosemary and allspice. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and vinegar. Spoon over each chicken breast.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Baste often with sauce during cooking. Serves 6.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Put butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and melt.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs and sugar.

Press with spoon to form crust. Scatter chocolate chips and nuts over crust, then the coconut. Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over top and bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until slightly brown around edges.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Take 2 packages crescent rolls. Roll out flat on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Combine ingredients.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chips and butter.
Cool.
Add marshmallows and pecans. Mix well.
Grease waxed paper and hands.
Roll in log on paper. Chill.

title: pralines
directions: Bring to boil.
Boil to 238°.
Remove; beat 3 to 4 minutes. Drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.

title: easy fixin supper
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in bottom of baking dish (about 3 layers).
Place 1 layer of onions on potatoes.
Add 3 or 4 more layers of potatoes.
Add 5 or 6 pieces of sausage on top of potatoes.
Cover dish and put in oven until potatoes are tender.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt stick butter in 3 to 4-quart saucepan. Add flour, finely chopped onions and dash of salt and pepper. Add finely chopped broccoli, chicken broth, half and half and water. Lightly salt to taste! Let boil and simmer over very low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rice may be cooked in water or milk.
Stir into milk. Add sugar, salt and eggs, slightly beaten.
One tablespoon butter may be added.
Flavor as desired (cinnamon).
Bake or steam in buttered shallow baking dish until firm.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan over medium heat until it boils.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chips together and spread over Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix and sift flour and sugar.
Make a well in the flour.
Add Crisco and milk.
Mix with hand or spoon.
Knead and roll out a floured board.
Cut to desired thickness.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: bisquick pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend at high speed until smooth.
Pour mixture into a deep pie plate that has been greased. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen peaches
directions: Make a simple syrup by mixing sugar and water and cooking until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and add juice.
Peel and slice peaches, place into containers, cover with juice solution and freeze.

title: raisin apple coffee cake
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Press thinly sliced apples on top of mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: boston cream pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef with onion, garlic powder and oregano; drain well and add 1 jar spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles according to package; drain and cool.
Mix cheeses and egg.
Cover the bottom of a large casserole with 1/2 of the second jar of spaghetti sauce, then a layer of noodles, a layer of ground beef mixture, a layer of cheese and remaining noodles.
Cover top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, cracker crumbs and almonds in a bowl. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Mix cracker crumbs and butter together and sprinkle over casserole. Top with almonds. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: religious sauce
directions: Grind onions and peppers together.
Add 1/2 cup water, if not enough juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add catsup, sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Use salt and allspice to taste.
Bring to a boil again and put into sterilized jars.
Process in hot water boiling bath for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Mix flour, soda and sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Heat buttermilk (measure buttermilk after it's been heated).
Add the yeast and buttermilk, then mix all ingredients.
Makes about 30 large rolls.
Store in containers in refrigerator.
Melt butter and pour on top of rolls before baking. Bake at 350° until you feel they are done.

title: skillet pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops on both sides in large skillet; drain on paper towels.
Drain off pan drippings.
Combine soup, water and seasonings; stir into skillet.
Return chops to skillet; add vegetables.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chops and vegetables are tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil spaghetti until al dente; drain.
Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli and garlic and saute for 3 minutes, then transfer to a heated dish.
Add chicken to the skillet and saute until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Toss pasta with broccoli and chicken.
Garnish with parsley.
Sprinkle with pepper and serve.

title: mexican stew
directions: Slice sausage into bite-sized pieces.
Combine with next 8 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until sausage is cooked through and vegetables are tender.
Place cheese cubes in serving bowls.
Ladle stew into bowls.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant until tender. Drain well and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and milk; blend in egg.
Add drained eggplant, onion and stuffing mix. Toss lightly with fork.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle top with more stuffing mix and dot with butter. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter frappe
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender for 45 seconds to 1 minute on highest speed.
Pour and enjoy!
Makes 1 large frappe.

title: 8-minute light 'n fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice using wire whip.
Blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill if necessary until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients except soup mix and chicken.
Place chicken on top, then sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Keep in a large tightly covered jar.
Use 2 teaspoons for each cup with hot water, or make it iced.
Can use peppermint candy in cup.

title: oven gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain potatoes and dry slices well. Place in bowl.
Mix savory, cayenne pepper, white pepper and parsley together.
Add to potatoes and mix.
Rub baking dish with garlic clove.
Butter dish generously and arrange potato slices in layers.
Season with salt.
Mix eggs, milk and cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked potato strips
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place potato strips in medium mixing bowl.
Drizzle with oil and toss to coat evenly.
Place potatoes on nonstick baking sheet in a single layer.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake 15 minutes more or longer for desired crispness.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Serve with oven fried chicken, if desired.

title: sherry cake
directions: Beat 1 cup sugar, egg yolks and sherry. Cook in heavy saucepan stirring constantly until thick. Soak gelatin in milk and stir into hot custard. Cool. Whip cream until soft peaks form. Gradually add other cup of sugar and whip until stiff. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into whipped cream. Fold in cooled custard. Tear cake into small pieces. In a large tube pan, add one layer of torn cake, then custard. Add another layer of cake, then custard. Layer until complete. Use more custard than cake. Chill 24 hours. Unmold and slice.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store.
Makes a large quantity. To serve, stir 3 teaspoons or to taste in a cup of hot water. Makes a great winter drink.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine dry ingredients in top of double boiler; add vinegar and water.
Cook 20 minutes over boiling water.
Yield:
2 cups sauce.
Serve over fresh pork or ham.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Remove seeds and pith from chilies.
Cut Jack cheese into chunks and divide evenly among the chilies, folding or tucking the cheese inside.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and arrange chilies side by side in the bottom.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In a large skillet, saut mushrooms and onions in hot butter until golden brown. Remove from skillet and set aside. Add bacon to skillet and fry until crisp. Remove and reserve. Add steak to skillet and fry bacon fat until well browned. Return mushrooms and onions to skillet and add flour. Toss until flour disappears. Add wine, beef broth, bay leaf, garlic and thyme. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Add carrots and bacon and cook, covered, another 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf. Season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with parsley. Serve over hot buttered noodles. Serves 3 to 4.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a large nonstick pan, melt margarine. Add garlic, cooking and stirring as needed until softened. Add broth, tomatoes and 3 cups water. Bring to a boil. Add the tortellini and return to a boil. Reduce and simmer about 10 minutes. Stir in spinach and return to a boil. Serve sprinkled with pepper.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place peeled and cut-up vegetables in the bottom of crock-pot. Top with roast.
Pour Lipton soup mix over that; no mixing needed. Then add mushroom soup.
Rinse soup can with small amount of water. When done, gravy is already made.
Cook on high approximately 5 hours or on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle chopped green onion for garnish.
Serve with crackers, chips or vegetable sticks.

title: spice rub
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in sealed shaker jar. Apply liberally and rub into meat at least 1 hour before grilling.

title: chicken broccoli cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
With meat mallet or rolling pin, pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness. Place a ham slice and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly roll fashion.
Tuck in ham and cheese if necessary; secure with wooden toothpicks.
In a 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk, green onions and thyme.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.

title: honey spice cookies
directions: Heat honey and molasses to boiling.
Cool completely.
Mix sugar, lemon peel and juice and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on floured cloth.
Cut into rectangles 1 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches or cut with cookie cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Then cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar into water; add frozen juices.
Mix well. Place in refrigerator.

title: ravishing rice
directions: Cook rice and soup mix in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Do not drain.
Cook sausage in skillet, separating with a fork; drain. Add sausage, celery, onion and pepper to rice; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets in salted water until tender; peel, cut and pack beets in hot sterilized jars.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and spice.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Pour over beets and seal jars.

title: diet pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl, except milk.
Gradually add milk; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie crust. Bake for 1 hour.

title: ratatouille - southern style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine onion, pepper, zucchini, okra, tomatoes, tomato liquid and bouillon in well-greased covered casserole.
Add basil, parsley and black pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Uncover the last 30 minutes to cook down juices.
Serve with bowl of grated cheese to sprinkle on each portion.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour pudding over above ingredients.
Mix.
Chill in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into 1-inch balls. Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet and freeze.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and celery until tender.
Add catsup, tomatoes, water, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes, then add tapioca and cook until thick.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine rice (uncooked) with beef, egg, onion, salt, marjoram, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice; mix lightly.
Shape mixture into 18 balls and place in skillet.
Pour the remaining 2 cups tomato juice over the meat balls.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or longer, until done, turning once and basting occasionally.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all together until Jell-O and Kool-Aid are completely dissolved, then add 2 cups of cold water and stir.
Pour into mold and freeze.
Makes 18 popsicles.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Combine turkey giblets, except the liver, with water, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to gentle boil.
Lower heat and cover. Simmer 1 hour or until giblets are tender.
Add the liver; simmer 15 minutes longer.
Drain mixture, reserving 1 cup of broth. Finely chop giblets and set aside.
Melt butter in medium size pan; stir in flour until smooth.
Add reserved cup of broth.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Stir in milk and chopped giblets.
Season to taste.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Grease 18 muffin cups.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl sift flour, baking soda, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add carrots, raisins, apple, nuts and coconut.
In another bowl stir together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add these to the flour mixture until batter becomes moist.
Fill muffin pans and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, adding vegetables with seasoning packet. Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.

title: pork roast - herb topping
directions: Mix all.
Slit pocket inside and stuff.
Rub on outside as well.
Roast at 350° for 20 minutes per pound.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Put cooked apples, sugar and vinegar in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 12 hours.
Add spices and cook on High for 3 hours, uncovered.
Seal in jars.

title: girl scout shortbread cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the shortening, sugar, vanilla and salt with an electric mixer.
Add the egg and beat the mixture until it's fluffy.
Add the baking soda and mix for about 20 seconds, then add the buttermilk and mix for an additional 30 seconds.
In another bowl, combine the flour and baking powder. Pour dry ingredients into wet ingredients and mix well with an electric mixer until flour is incorporated.
Roll the dough into a ball, cover it with plastic wrap and chill for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, drain off all liquid and remove the garlic.

title: holly's quick brownies
directions: Melt together margarine and unsweetened chocolate or cocoa. Cream sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate mixture, flour and vanilla. Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased pan.

title: cream cheese spinach dip
directions: In a bowl cream the cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Add the Ranch dressing and beat.
Drain frozen spinach and add to the mixture.
Cut the center out of the bread; use these pieces for dipping.
Fill the center of bread with mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute in butter until tender the onion, pimento and bell pepper.
Mix corn, rice, eggs and Cheddar cheese.
Top with 1/2 to 3/4 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: supper surprise
directions: Prepare Hamburger Helper.
When it's done, add soup and green beans.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Eat.
Very good.

title: hot dogs on bun
directions: Boil 8 Ball Park hot dogs in boiling water.
Garnish with mustard, ketchup, relish and onions.

title: fudge pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and Crisco, beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beat well after each egg.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt, and baking powder together; add to other ingredients and beat well. Pour in tube pan that has been lightly greased and dusted with flour.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325 degrees or until cake is done.

title: tuna and water chestnut casserole
directions: Chop water chestnuts into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Add rest of ingredients and mix. Cover top with crushed potato chips. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: potatoes delmonico en casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a heavy baking dish that can be used for serving.
In a medium saucepan, heat the butter and whisk in flour, whisking until bubbly, about 2 to 3 minutes, but do not let brown.
Remove
from heat and whisk in
milk, beating vigorously to blend well.
Return to moderate heat.
Add dash of salt and pepper.
Add garlic powder.
Cook and stir until sauce is thickened and smooth.
Add the grated cheese and stir until melted.
Place the potatoes in baking dish and pour sauce over them.
Mix gently with a wooden spatula in order not to break up the potato slices.
Sprinkle the top with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Blend flour, salt and baking soda. Mix corn flakes, oats and nuts. Combine all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwich dip
directions: Add mayonnaise for consistency desired.
Mix and store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 4 dozen small sandwiches or 1 pint.

title: war cake 1943
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients for 5 minutes.
When cool, add soda mixture.
Add nuts and flour mixture.
Put in 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hi rise salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add drained pineapple, diced bananas and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice squash into 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil 3 minutes or until tender.
Drain; add onion and beaten eggs, mixed with seasonings. Melt butter and stir into cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over squash. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice 20
minutes.
Pour boiling water over broccoli. Saute onions and
celery
in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into
a
large casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown the hamburger in a skillet until it loses its reddish color.
Add the onion and continue to cook until onion is glazed and transparent.
Add the salt and pepper.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, while scraping bowl.
Beat on high for 5 minutes, still scraping the bowl.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt slowly with milk on low speed.
Pour into pan and bake until toothpick comes out clean, 70 to 80 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: lemonade fruit bowl
directions: In a large bowl, mix fruits, raisins, concentrate and honey. Just before serving, stir in Muesli.
Spoon into 4 bowls, dividing equally.
Top with yogurt, dividing equally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet over medium heat until crisp. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic to reserved drippings and cook over medium heat until tender and most of mushroom liquid has evaporated, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper.
Add cream cheese, Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Reduce heat to low and stir until cheese is melted. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and bacon.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: holiday salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in hot applesauce.
Combine remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine thoroughly.
Beat until light. Bear in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Stir all ingredients together in bowl.
Make into balls like marbles.
Dip into sugar.
Put on greased pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Saute apples and butter in pan on medium heat for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients (sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg).
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes in covered pan.
Mix flour and salt together.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir with wire whisk until well blended.
Pour into ovenproof skillet with 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Pancakes will fluff up.
You will need to punch down with fork.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: crispy baked fillets
directions: Wash and dry fillets and cut into serving pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat with corn flake crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes without turning or basting.
This method produces a crisp coating.
Looks almost like deep-fried fish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa, then add milk.
Beat eggs and mix. Add butter last.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cook ingredients in a double boiler.

title: quick linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine in Dutch oven according to package directions. Drain and return to Dutch oven.
Saute garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil in skillet.
Add clams and next 5 ingredients.
Cook on low, stirring constantly 5 minutes.
Pour over hot linguine and toss.
Place on warm platter.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, blend well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: date bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put butter and baking soda into a 1-cup measuring cup.
Fill up to one cup with boiling water.
In a bowl, place dates and nuts and pour boiling water over them.
Cool.
Mix in sugar, egg yolk, flour, vanilla and salt.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Slice and serve with butter and cream cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray Pam into 10-inch casserole dish.
If using sausage, brown and drain.
Place cubed bread in bottom of dish.
Layer meat over bread.
Layer cheese over meat.
Beat eggs and milk with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except for pie filling. Put 1/2 dough in bottom of cake pan. Then layer on pie filling. Spread remaining dough on top. Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain, re-cover with water and bring to boil.
Simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Drain bean juice and reserve 1 to 2 cups.
Add remaining ingredients to beans and mix.
Pour mixture into a bean pot or large casserole bowl.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 to 7 hours.
If liquid evaporates below level of beans, add beer or reserved bean juice.
Remove cover the last 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Stir in butter and peanut butter until dissolved.
Remove from heat and pour mixture over cornflakes.
Stir until all flakes are coated.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Cool and enjoy!
Makes 25 or more, depending on the size.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Spread slices generously with butter.
Arrange in buttered dish with buttered side down.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
Strain and pour over bread.
Let stand 30 minutes. Bake one hour in slow oven.
Cover the first half hour of baking. The top of pudding should be well browned.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and margarine in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, vanilla extract and almond extract.
Beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
May freeze for later use.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: party sausages
directions: Put all of the ingredients into a crock-pot on low until heated through and through.
Serve while hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well and fold in carrots.
Mix well and pour in three pans and bake at 375° until done.

title: authentic italian pizza
directions: Dissolve the warm water and yeast together and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Let rise until doubled.
Pat into 12-inch pizza pan, forming sides.

title: goulash
directions: *Those with no or low salt diets, use salt substitute.
It's great!

title: holiday strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Stir carefully. Turn batter into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Turn out onto cooling racks. This makes 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup. Pat remaining batter into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour with salt and pepper and pound into meat.
In preheated skillet at 325°, melt shortening.
Brown meat on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to 225°.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with vegetable gravy. Makes 6 servings.

title: old english casserole
directions: Place cooked noodles in a lightly greased 8-cup baking dish. Brown beef in a large skillet.
Remove meat to a bowl; drain all but 1 tablespoon fat from skillet.
Saute onion in fat in skillet until tender.
Return beef.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix package of pudding with 1 cup milk.
Mix Cool Whip gradually.
You may not need the entire bowl.
Next, add the Snicker pieces.
Mix well, then add apple pieces and mix well. Should end up with a thick consistency and absolutely no calories!

title: microwave zucchini one-dish meal
directions: In shallow 3-quart casserole, mix oil and next 3 ingredients. Add potatoes, onions and zucchini, turning to coat all sides. Cook, covered, on High 12 minutes until potatoes are tender; stir often.
Add peppers.
Cook, covered, on High for 10 minutes more. When vegetables are all done, sprinkle with shredded cheese and cook 1 minute more until melted.
Makes 4 servings.
About 370 calories per serving.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together 2 cups light brown sugar and 3/4 cup margarine. Then add cold water.
Stir in remaining ingredients slowly until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon on a buttered pan.
If dough is not stiff enough, add more flour.
Before baking, cut a maraschino cherry, place cut side down and bake.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks well; add milk and then sifted dry ingredients and the melted butter.
Add the well drained corn and drop by spoonfuls into deep 375° fat and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot with maple syrup.

title: albondigas(mexican meatballs)
directions: Mix hamburger meat with rice and roll into small balls. Saute onion in
margarine.
Add
tomatoes,
garlic,
salt
and oregano. Add 1 can
of
water
and bring to a boil.	Drop your hamburger and rice
balls
into the boiling ingredients. Cover and simmer until meatballs look done.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt cake pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini and cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased cake pan (or large Bundt pan) or 3 loaves.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Good with cream cheese.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion and pepper in oil using 10-inch frypan with lid.
When meat has browned, arrange following on top in layers in order given:
rice, corn, tomatoes, salt, cheese, olives and olive juice.
Cover pan tightly.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to simmer and cook 15 minutes.
Serve from frypan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup mixture and cheese in buttered casserole. Dot top with margarine and sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: In heavy soup kettle, melt butter.
Add oil.
Add onion, scallions and garlic.
Add celery and cauliflower.
Add seasonings.
Mix well and cook, uncovered, over medium heat for several minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water and miso.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
Remove cover and slightly cool.

title: venison sauerbraten
directions: Place venison in earthenware bowl or glass baking dish with onions, bay leaves, peppercorn, cloves, berries, salt, vinegar and boiling water.
Cover tightly; refrigerate at least 3 days, turning meat twice a day.
Never pierce meat when turning.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.
In heavy skillet, brown meat on all sides in shortening.
Add marinade mixture, Cover tightly; simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and onions from skillet and keep warm.
Strain and measure liquid in skillet; add water, if needed to measure 2 1/2 c. liquid.
Pour liquid into skillet, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir gingersnaps and sugar into liquid. Cover; simmer gently 3 minutes.
Serve meat and onions on a platter.
Accompany with gingersnap gravy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt drippings in 10-inch iron skillet in hot oven (425°). Add milk, egg and drippings to corn meal.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into hot, prepared skillet.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press rolls flat on cookie sheet and bake until brown in 350° oven (about 7 to 8 minutes).
Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped veggies and Cheddar cheese.

title: mama's meat and veggies("goo-laush")
directions: Put ground meat in large skillet in a small amount of Crisco oil.
Add chopped onions, peppers, salt and black pepper.
Let cook until meat is half done, but not brown or crispy.
Drain some of the fat.
Add mixed veggies.
Let cook on low temperature until all is done.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: broccoli with almonds
directions: Cut bacon slices into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place bacon pieces in large skillet; cook over medium heat until bacon is golden brown, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer cooked bacon to paper towels to drain; set aside.
Pour off bacon fat from skillet; return 1 tablespoon bacon fat to skillet.
Cut garlic cloves into very thin slivers.
Add olive oil and garlic to skillet; saute until garlic is golden brown, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.

title: simple rice dish
directions: Saute the onion and celery in margarine.
Pour the rice, beef consomme and mushrooms in pan.
Cook until consomme is absorbed in rice.
This is a good side dish with steaks or chops.

title: lumpia(egg rolls)
directions: Chop that all really fine - and you can add bean sprouts, cabbage, etc. if you want.
Brown everything together and drain the meat mixture really good.
Let it cool for a little bit.
Take your lumpia wrappers and put one large spoonful of meat mixture in one of the corners.
Start rolling and half way fold the ends in and then continue.
Make sure you wrap it really tight.
Take flour and water mixture and just use that as like a glue to make the end stick together.
Fry in regular oil until golden brown.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Put in a shallow baking pan.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Alternately, add pumpkin and dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in bits.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Combine salt, thyme, marjoram, celery salt and pepper.
Rub chicken with seasonings.
Rub cavity of bird with additional salt. Skewer neck skin to back.
Tie legs to tail; twist wings under back.
Place chicken in pot, breast side up.
Cover tightly; place in unheated oven.
Turn oven to 400° and bake until chicken is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean-corn casserole
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish and mix well. Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine, then sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together in a bowl that can be covered and keep in refrigerator overnight.
Keep mixed well; it will keep for several days.

title: sour cream posy rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, granulated sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat sour cream, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Stir into dry ingredients.
Mix 1 egg and enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth (about 4 minutes).
Divide into 12 equal pieces.
Roll into smooth ball.
Place on greased baking sheet; cover.
Place large shallow pan on counter, half-fill with boiling water.
Place back in sheet over pan.
Let rise 20 minutes.
With scissors, make 6 (3/4-inch) deep around outside of each roll.
Beat remaining egg and brush on rolls.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done. Remove from sheet; cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: pepper steak
directions: Toss steak strips with flour, coating well.
Brown in oil. Drain well.
Add soup, water and catsup.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Add bell pepper and cook 30 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put milk, chocolate morsels, marshmallows and salt into a heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt completely and mixture thickens.
Take off heat. Cool to room temperature.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan with vanilla wafers.
Spoon half of 1 quart vanilla ice cream over the wafers.
Cover with half of chocolate mixture.
Place whole nuts on top.
Freeze until firm, 3 to 5 hours.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, salt, eggs, grated orange rind and orange juice. Stir in dry ingredients (which have been sifted together).
Add nut meats and blend well. Drop from teaspoon on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Cover with Orange Icing while warm.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Cook pasta until half done.
While this is cooking, chop broccoli and slice mushrooms.
Drain pasta; return to pan and add broccoli, mushrooms, margarine, minced garlic, chicken stock, half and half and milk.
Cook until pasta is done and broccoli is tender-crisp.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Add more if needed to make right consistency to serve.

title: beer batter
directions: Pour beer into a bowl, add flour.
Mixture will foam.
Stir in salt, paprika and baking powder.
If using to fry fruit, you may want to use cinnamon or nutmeg instead of paprika.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving oil.
Saute onion and garlic in artichoke oil until clear.
Beat eggs; add bread crumbs, seasonings, cheese and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Spray quiche pan or 9 x 13-inch pan with oil.
Spread evenly.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares if using 9 x 13-inch pan. Can reheat to serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and serve on lettuce.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Put onions and jalapenos in blender until finely chopped. Add spices and drained tomatoes and pulse just till well blended.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together, except Ritz crackers and melted butter. Crush Ritz crackers and put on top of casserole with melted butter. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies on pizza pan close together.
Cook and let cool. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip and spread on crust. Mix other ingredients and glaze.
Pour on top and chill.
Other fruits can be used.
Serve with Cool Whip on serving plate.
