title: finger wings
directions: Bake chicken wings at 400° for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until thickens.
Brush over chicken wings. Continue baking, turning and brushing until all the mixture is used.
Cook about 40 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all together, add nuts if you wish.
Spread in cookie sheet and sprinkle small package of chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: veal oscar
directions: Clean and dry fish. Cut into pieces. Dip in 1 cup milk after having salted it. Then dredge in bread crumbs. Place in baking dish with a little olive oil and a little butter; no water. Brown quickly in very hot oven.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Preheat
oven
In large bowl, combine sugars, flour and
cinnamon.
Add
fruit
and mix well.
Turn into pie shell. Dot
with
butter.
Cover; seal edges and cut slits in top crust. Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: Mix liquid ingredients, then add all dry ingredients.
Make into small cookies approximately heaping teaspoonful, as they will spread in cooking.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
In glass oven may use 325°
for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.
Do not brown as they are very short and will burn easily.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In a bowl in the microwave, heat cheese until melted.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chili and heat until soft.
It is good to keep this in a fondue dish or small crockette pot.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut into diagonal slices about 1-inch long.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender; drain and cool.
Combine carrots, onion and green pepper in a large bowl.

title: speedy salmon patties
directions: In a bowl, combine salmon, onion, egg, saltines, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Shape into 6 patties. In a skillet, fry patties in butter over medium heat for
3 to 4 minutes on each side. Yield: 3 servings.

title: golden chicken drummettes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients for a marinade.
Place in large bowl; add drummettes and stir to coat all pieces.
Set aside for 30 minutes.
In a shallow bowl, combine corn flakes, walnuts and wheat germ.
Dip drummettes in flour, then egg whites and roll in corn flake mixture.
Shake off any excess coating.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place drummettes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, crushed berries and water.
Cook on low heat stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool. Place whole berries in pie shell.
Pour over berries in shell and chill until firm.
Add whipped topping.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Prepare vanilla sauce according to directions on box.
Add pineapple to prepared sauce.
Place mixture between each layer.
Add whipping cream to top of cake; decorate with Mandarin oranges.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together and make into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake quartered biscuits in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Melt brown sugar and margarine in pan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Arrange biscuits in Bundt pan.
Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Turn Bundt pan over on plate.
Enjoy.

title: oven made caramel corn
directions: Combine popped corn, roasted peanuts and pecans in a large roasting pan.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; stir in sugars, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes, stir often (temperature will be about 244°).
Remove from heat; stir in soda. Pour sugar mixture over popped corn and nuts; stir well.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: In large skillet brown beef with onion.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder; drain fat.
In medium bowl combine sour cream, soup and green chilies; blend well.
Spoon half this mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon 2 heaping tablespoons of meat mixture into a tortilla.
Top with sprinkling of grated cheese and roll up.
Place seam side down in baking dish on top of sour cream mixture.
Repeat until all tortillas are used.
Pour remaining sour cream mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle any remaining ground beef and cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until sauce bubbles and cheese is melted. Remove from oven and top with picante sauce as desired.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored. Gradually beat in sugar. Stir in oil, then zucchini.

title: apple sundae pudding
directions: Core, peel and slice apples. Place in 2-quart baking dish. Sift together dry ingredients: flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt, cinnamon and 2/3 cup granulated sugar. In another bowl, combine nuts, milk, melted butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients and spread on top of apples in baking dish. Mix together brown sugar, 1/4 cup granulated sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Sprinkle on top of mixture in baking dish. Pour boiling water over all. Do not stir. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Cover and bake for 30 more minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice and core apples.
Spread into a large baking pan.
Put over top of apples 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons water.
In a bowl, put in Bisquick, cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
In a separate small bowl, beat egg.
Mix egg into Bisquick mix and toss around until crumbly.
Pour that mixture over top of apples and pour melted butter over that.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients; chill dough.
Roll thin and slice. Bake in moderate oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: brown rice
directions: Add salt and pepper for taste. Cook in a 350° oven, uncovered, for about 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into 2-quart buttered casserole or baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, uncovered.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Bake ham at 325° for 20 minutes per pound.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Put nectar in pan and bring to a boil.
While still hot, add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Let set until it cools for a time and then add pineapple with juice, nuts and crumbled cream cheese.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine egg and milk, set aside.
Combine corn meal, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomatoes in egg mixture, then roll in corn meal mixture.
Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Arrange in single layers of tomato slices.
Cook until golden brown on each side.

title: hamburg macaroni casserole
directions: Mix browned hamburg and cooked macaroni together.
Add cream of celery soup and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Reduce to 350° after putting cake in. Let rolls thaw 10 minutes outside package.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Melt margarine and mix in sugar, pudding mix and cinnamon.
Roll each piece of the roll into the mixture.
Layer the pieces in a Bundt pan.
After the 1st layer, sprinkle nuts or other choice.
Continue layering.
Let rise overnight in a warm place.
Do not cover.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: best pecan pie
directions: The secret is to bring the first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil for 3 or 4 minutes.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs and 1 cup of pecans.
Blend well with cooked mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat all, except cake mix, butter and nuts.
Pour into ungreased, 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: walking taco dip
directions: Cook meat and add about 1/2 package taco seasoning.

Let cool. In a glass pie plate, put first layer of refried beans; second layer of meat; third layer of chopped scallions; fourth layer chopped tomatoes; fifth layer halved olives; sixth layer cheese. Chill.
When ready to serve, top with sour cream and salsa.
Serve with taco chips.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: cantaloupe salad
directions: Heat orange juice to boiling.
Dissolve Jello in hot juice. Chill until partially set.
Fold in cantaloupe and Cool Whip. Chill until firm.

title: busy woman's slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, seed and salt in saucepan.
Simmer for 6 minutes.
Stir always.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage, pepper and onion.
Mix with spoon or your hands.
Store
in gallon jar for 24 hours before serving.
Will stay fresh for 3 to 4 weeks.
Keep refrigerated.

title: homemade graham cracker crust
directions: Toss crumbs with melted butter or margarine in medium size bowl.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with vegetable cooking spray. Press crumb mixture evenly over bottom and sides of plate.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden; be careful not to overbake.
Cool completely before filling.

title: vegetable salad(pea salad)
directions: Drain all vegetables,
chop
vegetables that have to be chopped.
Bring to a
boil the sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and celery seed.
Let
cool.
Mix
all together and let set 24 hours before eating.
Can eat if sets overnight.

title: butter-nut roll
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and cream cheese.
Beat well.
Slowly add flour and eggs a little at a time.
Put aside 1/4 cup flour.
Mix separately nuts, chips and 1/4 cup flour.
Slowly add vanilla to well beaten batter.
Pour one layer into Bundt pan, then center nut mixture; then more batter on top.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours, or until done.
Cool 45 minutes, take out of pan.
Slice gently and eat!!

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes(serves 12)
directions: Do not refrigerate while making.
Use a plastic container.
Do not use a metal spoon or electric mixer.

title: lime-vegetable salad
directions: Boil water.
Pour over jello.
Add vegetables and cottage cheese.
Pour into individual molds or one large dish.

title: crab dip
directions: Pick over crabmeat and remove any cartilage.
Flake with fork. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; chill.
Serve with crackers and celery sticks.

title: best-ever pancakes
directions: Make batter by stirring ingredients in order given.
Fold in egg whites last. If batter is too stiff, add more sour milk.
Bake on hot griddle or pan.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: plaki (greek fish)
directions: Saute onions and garlic in small amount olive oil.
Clean fish and rub with lemon juice and salt.
Add to pot.
Pour crushed tomatoes over and small amount of water.
Sprinkle generously with mint flakes, parsley and raisins.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: lavona's pie crust
directions: Finger first three ingredients together until crumbly.
Whip together egg, water and vinegar, then add to flour mixture.
Fork until sticks together and pat into 3 balls, let stand for 5 minutes.
Roll into 3 single crusts and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make small patties out of ground beef; brown on both sides. Add diced onion, potatoes, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add water. Cover; simmer until potatoes and onion are tender.

title: dijon chicken breasts
directions: Stir together salad dressing or mayonnaise and seasonings in a small bowl.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 20 minutes longer. Place chicken on greased grill or rack of broiler pan.
Grill or broil until tender, 10 minutes each side, brushing frequently with marinade mixture.

title: pecan crumb tarts
directions: Blend together graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar. Divide mixture in 8 paper cups.
Set in muffin tins.
Press crumb mixture firmly against bottom and sides of cups with a small custard cup or glass.
Refrigerate while preparing filling.
When filling has cooled, put into tart shells and sprinkle with mixture of coconut and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Place strawberries, jello and sugar in a saucepan on low heat and let jello and sugar melt.
Set aside.
Put the cold milk, one carton of Cool Whip, sour cream and instant pudding in a bowl; beat with an electric beater.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of strawberries and a layer of pudding mix in a clear glass bowl.
Repeat layers.
Put Cool Whip on top and garnish with strawberries.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
Mix quickly.
Dip out by teaspoon on to wax paper and cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken satay
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch strips and knead with the next 7 ingredients, adding one at a time.
Marinate for at least 2 hours.

title: country steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Dredge in flour and pound with back of butcher knife or use a meat mallet.
Brown on both sides in small amount of hot oil.
Remove meat to a platter and drain excess fat from pan.
Turn heat to low.
Return meat to pan and cover with mushrooms and soup and water mixture.
Cover pan with lid and simmer for 35 to 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Great served with mashed potatoes.

title: quickie beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into small pieces and brown.
Add soup mix, beef cubes and water.
Simmer until tender.
Add sour cream until desired consistency.
Serve over rice.

title: sara's pepper steak
directions: In

a large skillet, saute garlic in butter. Add meat and brown. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and sherry. Simmer. In another pan, cook mushrooms in oil for 5 minutes. To the mushrooms, add 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and green peppers. Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Add to meat mixture along with tomatoes and heat thoroughly. Serve over white rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: sugar-free cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add the Equal; let set for 30 minutes, while mixing the Jell-O as directed on the box, letting it set until thickened, but not set firm.
Add all remaining ingredients. Let set until firm.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease 12-cup tube pan.
In large bowl, cream margarine.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Stir in flour, dry frosting mix and nuts until blended.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Tear cheese into small pieces.
Bring salted water to a boil; slowly add grits.
Bring to second boil.
Reduce heat and cook over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add cheese and butter, stirring until well blended.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Good with ham.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to boiling until sugar dissolves and pour over vegetables.
Keep in covered container and chill for 24 hours.
May be kept in refrigerator up to 10 days.

title: seafood dip
directions: Melt cheese and butter together over medium heat.
Stir until melted.
Add pimentos, crab meat and shrimp (if desired).
Mix together well.
Add dry sherry.
More may be added as needed to thin mixture.
Serve warm with corn chips and/or crackers.

title: fruit cake
directions: Use 1 cup flour to dredge fruit.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add molasses, then beaten egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with liquid.
Fold in fruit and nuts (use hands).
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pack in pans. Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 275°.
Line pans with 2 layers oiled brown paper bags.
Set pan of water on bottom rack of oven. If you need more liquid, use orange juice, only after you use egg whites.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and garlic until meat loses its color. Add rest of ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Chop onion fine; add raw hamburger meat and in large skillet cook slowly until done.
Add Worcestershire sauce, parsley, Italian seasoning, chili powder, garlic salt, tomatoes, tomato paste and Parmesan cheese.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring frequently.
When thick, remove from heat; let set about 10 minutes, then skim off grease.
Cook noodles according to package. Pour off water, then add cold water to cover.
(This keeps noodles loose.)
In a large 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, put in a layer of noodles, a layer of meat, layer of cottage cheese to which eggs have been added, a layer of Mozzarella and a layer of sauce.
Repeat with meat mixture being top layer.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour in a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Stick toothpick in cake until it comes out clean.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat, onion and seasonings.
Pour off all grease.
Put in beans and tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Pour dressing over this when ready to serve.
Mix with meat and Fritos.

title: sweet and sour chicken breasts
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake date bars
directions: In saucepan, cook dates, margarine and honey until thick and blended.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats, coconut and walnuts.
Press mixture into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Let cool, then store in airtight storage container.

title: beef ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Chop beef.
Mix together onion, cream cheese, beef, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into a ball.
Let set overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat margarine, then add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: noodles and ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions with salt. Drain.
Brown the meat with onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Drain the grease off meat.
Stir butter into the noodles and blend it into the meat.
Combine the tomato soup, water and cheese to noodles and meat.
Mix well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: stuffed whole tomato
directions: Wash tomato and remove the center.
Sprinkle the hollow with a bit of salt and pepper.
Mix rice with tomato and the ground meat. Refill the center of the tomato with mixture.
Place butter on top of tomato and set in a lightly buttered pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Contains 186 calories per serving.

title: spicy viva la pasta
directions: Cook rotini according to package; drain.
Cook sausage, breaking up coarsely in medium size skillet until lightly browned. Drain.
Combine rotini, sausage, corn, kidney beans, tomatoes, green olives, bell pepper, ripe olives and Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Blend tomatoes with green chiles in small bowl with oil, seasoned salt and basil.
Add to other ingredients; toss until well coated.
Chill well.
Toss before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans with ground beef
directions: Brown beef/ground chuck, onion and bell pepper lightly and drain fat. Add remaining ingredients. Place in baking dish. Place strips of bacon on top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Cook peaches, water and honey until peaches are soft; sieve. Stir in lemon juice, almond extract and apple juice.
Chill until cool.

title: easy steak
directions: Season the steak and place on a large piece of heavy foil. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over the steak.
Sprinkle on 2 tablespoons water.
Pour brown gravy over this.
Roll edges tight on foil and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot and orange soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add onions.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 25 minutes.
Add carrots and broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until carrots are very tender, about 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package label directs.
Drain.
Meanwhile, prepare seasoning mix with ground chuck, tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1 1/4 cups water as package label directs.
Preheat oven to 350° now.

title: salt substitute
directions: Combine and after mixing well, store in a spice shaker with a tight-fitting lid.
As with all spices, keep in a cool, dry place.

title: three-step cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients at medium speed until well blended.
Add the eggs; mix well.
Pour batter into the crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until center is almost set.
Cool. For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with blueberries or strawberries.

title: noodles and sauce
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix together the ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
Serve over noodles sprinkled with cheese.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Divide pastry into 2 parts and roll thin to fit an 8 or 9 inch pie plate.
Set aside.
Mix apples, cornstarch and spice. Stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into the pastry and top with the second piece of pastry.
Seal the edges and cut slits in the top.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: potato nachos
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Rinse and drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Brush baking sheet and potato slices with oil. Place slices in a single layer on baking sheet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Top each slice with cheese, tomato, chilies, olives and green onions.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer, until potatoes are tender and cheese is melted. Serve with salsa, sour cream and guacamole.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls; press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy greens
directions: Separate and wash greens.
Put all ingredients in a big pot. Half fill pot with water.
Cover pot with lid.
Cook on medium.

title: lye soap
directions: Mix lye and cold water together.
Stir with a wooden spoon. Use enamelware or glass container for this.
Water becomes very hot.
Set aside to cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain corn and set aside.
Beat eggs in a medium bowl and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, melt butter and then stir in flour. When flour and butter are mixed well, slowly pour in milk.
Keep stirring so flour won't lump up.
When milk is warm, stir in eggs rapidly and constantly so they don't curdle.
Remove from heat and add corn and rest of ingredients.
Return to heat and cook until hot.
Constantly stir so mixture will not scorch.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Place casserole dish in pan of warm water and bake at 350° until inserted knife comes out clean, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: south american chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; add coffee.
Stir well.
Cook over low heat 1 minute; remove.
Scald milk; add.
Simmer until piping hot.
Beat until frothy on top.
Set over hot water for 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: mozzarella sticks
directions: Dip cheese sticks in egg, then flour, egg and bread crumbs. Fry in very hot oil for 6 seconds.
Only fry 5 at a time.
Serve with leftover spaghetti sauce as dip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in heavy skillet until meat is browned.
Add seasoning and tomato soup; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine with vegetables cooked as directed on package.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with mounds of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done (and still hot), poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut and pour slowly over cake. Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.
Serve from pan.

title: gooey buns
directions: Grind bologna and cheese.
Add mustard, mayonnaise, onion and sweet pickles.
Mix well.
Cut buns in half.
Butter buns and fill with meat mixture.
Wrap in wax paper and heat at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: smores
directions: Break graham cracker in half. Take 1/2 graham cracker and put 1 hershey bar and 1 jumbo marshmallow on it. Top with the other 1/2 graham cracker. Melt in microwave. Make as many as you want.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Mix all together, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and butter.
Put vinegar into a pint cup.
Fill cup with water and add to the mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until done.

title: praline sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Cook and stir over low heat until sauce is smooth and syrupy, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and chopped pecans. Serve sauce warm over ice cream.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: bridget flynn's irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift the flour.
Add all the ingredients (will be dry; add a drop of milk if needed).
Let stand 10 minutes.
Will make 2 loaves.
Place the mixture in two loaf pans.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes, then cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Cool, peel and dice; set aside. In large pan, melt butter.
Turn off heat.
Add green onions, sour cream, chicken soup and grated cheese; mix well.
Add potatoes. Put in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until hot throughout.
Can be made a day ahead and kept in refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: hearty soup stock
directions: Put water in a large kettle or Dutch oven.
Add Hearty Soup Mix and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery, cabbage, tomato sauce and vegetable juice cocktail.
Add cooked ground beef or other meat, if desired. Simmer 20 more minutes, until vegetables are cooked.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add crackers, butter and 1 cup cheese; beat eggs lightly and add milk.
Mix with squash; sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix together graham crackers, sugar, egg yolks and walnuts. Then add stiffly beaten egg whites and baking powder.
Pour into well oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 300° oven. Cool completely.
If possible, bake the day before serving, and leave in pan covered with plastic wrap.
Cut into bite-size squares.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cut margarine into flour mixture with a fork until mealy. Add milk.
Mix gently. Drop large spoonfuls into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and milk together.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour cream cheese mixture over the angel food cake.
Pour cans of pie filling over the cream cheese mixture.
Place in refrigerator.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Cook chicken with oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven until chicken is opaque.
Add all ingredients except rice and boil gently for 10 minutes.
Add rice and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix and drop 1 teaspoon of dough on a slightly greased pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Drop 1 inch apart.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook squash in a little boiling salted water until tender; drain.
In a saucepan, cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in squash.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter and add to remaining stuffing cubes.
Toss gently and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate beer cake
directions: Mix boiling water and cocoa;
stir in beer and let stand to cool to lukewarm.

title: tomato surprise salad or relish
directions: Simmer tomatoes.
Add Jell-O, salt and vinegar.
Mold or return to can and mold.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, and beat until stiff.
Melt butter and add applesauce, mix together well.
Sift flour and measure into bowl, then add soda, salt and spices to flour.
Add small amounts at a time.
Bake in muffin tins, lined with paper cups.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix butter and seasoning.
Split rolls, a pan at a time, and spread butter mixture on rolls.
Spread ham and cheese over all. Re-assemble rolls and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 60.
These freeze well before or after baking.

title: minced eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant until done.
Chop fine.
Mix with the 1/2 bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour mixture in a baking dish sprayed well with nonstick spray, sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: nadine's beet cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together sugar, oil and vanilla until blended. Beat in eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Stir in flour mixture, a little at a time, until smooth.
Stir in beets and walnuts.
Turn into an oiled 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until done, circa 1 hour.
Loosen edges and turn out on a rack.
Place cake in a plastic bag and let stand overnight at room temperature.

title: coffee-coffee cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, coffee powder and salt.
Combine 3 tablespoons melted butter, milk, beaten egg and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until well blended.
Turn into greased 8-inch square pan or deep pie dish.
Combine corn flake crumbs, remaining 2 tablespoons melted butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Scatter evenly over batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm or cold.

title: scrambled tofu
directions: Crumble in pan (lightly greased).
Add other ingredients and heat.
Divide for small family.

title: skroodles salad
directions: Dice vegetables and set aside.
Cook and drain noodles.
Soak in cool water for 10 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Add Salad Supreme and Italian dressing to the noodles. Cover and refrigerate, the longer the better.
When ready to serve, add diced vegetables and toss lightly.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. In a medium bowl, mix 4 tablespoons butter, sugar, flour, vanilla and salt until smooth. Mix in rolled oats. Drop firmly packed spoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheets. Bake until golden brown. Rotate sheets halfway through baking (about 12 to 15 minutes). Cool on sheet 1 minute. Transfer with thin metal spatula onto paper towels and cool completely.

title: spicy bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients with spatula.
Add beans last.
Pour in greased 2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until beans are firm.

title: iowa chocolate cake
directions: Put shortening and sugar in mixing bowl; cover with boiling water.
Sift dry ingredients and add to hot mixture.
Then add eggs and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: grape juice crush
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.

title: fried chicken ii
directions: Thaw and cut chicken breast into 3 strips. Pound lightly on both sides with a meat hammer or saucer. Place in a microwave dish and microwave for 3 minutes; remove and cool chicken. Place in a bag large enough to accommodate the amount of chicken you prepare. Mix flour, chicken seasoning and other optional seasoning in a bag and shake until somewhat coated. Fry in a small amount of olive oil on medium heat for 5 minutes. Turn and repeat until golden brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat milk in double boiler; add egg yolks and sugar (reserve egg whites for meringue).
Make a paste using a little water and cornstarch.
Mix paste into milk mixture and add vanilla.
Stir constantly until very thick.
Add coconut to mixture (amount desired).
Pour filling into baked deep dish pie shells, cover with meringue and sprinkle peaks with coconut.
Bake at 375° just until it turns a little brown.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix all together.
Spread and press into 8 x 15-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Cut bread in half; cut off ends.
With fork, hollow out center of bread, leaving a thick crust as shell; reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
In skillet, combine beef, onion, oregano, salt and pepper; brown.
Remove from heat; add crumbs, mustard, parsley, egg and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Fill loaf with mixture.
Replace cut ends and secure with wooden picks.
Brush with melted butter; warp in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Loosen foil and continue to bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Slice stuffed bread loaf and serve with cheese sauce.

title: pizza appetizer fondue(serves 6)
directions: In fondue pot, over low heat, heat all ingredients (except bread) until cheese is melted and sauce is hot. Dip in chunks of bread.
Yum!

title: colonel cotton cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add crushed vanilla wafers alternately with milk. Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy.
Add pecans. Fold gently to coat. Mix spices and fold into pecan mix.
Put on lightly greased sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir every 10 minutes. Store in jar or plastic tub.

title: baked crab with port wine
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream, wine, capers, pimentos, mustard, salt, green onion and pepper sauce in medium bowl.
Stir in crabmeat carefully.
Divide mixture among four individual oven safe casseroles or ramekins.
Mix bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over each ramekin.
Cook uncovered in 375 F oven about 20 minutes. Garnish with parsley and lemon.
Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place over boiling water and beat with rotary beater until mixture holds its shape.
Fold in vanilla.
Beat until cool and spread.

title: sauteed garden veggies
directions: Saute ingredients in butter.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: In
mixing
bowl, combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg. Beat on medium speed until blended.
Batter will be very sticky. Drop
by
teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar; roll lightly
to coat.
Place
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients with blender or mixer.
Pour in a greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: white wine punch
directions: Using 3 to 4 inch cup, cut a round out of each slice of bread, reserving round for another use.
Melt butter in skillet and saute each slice of bread until bottom is brown.
Flip over and toast other side.
Crack 1 egg in hole; cover and cook until toast is done and egg is thoroughly done.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Slice and place in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, vanilla and margarine over low heat.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch. Stir in evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: good cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Work in vanilla, flour and nuts.
Shape into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on unoiled baking sheet and bake in moderate (350°) oven for 20 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Cut into 1/4-inch cubes, boiled ham and Cheddar cheese. Combine with
green
onions,
hard-cooked
eggs
and pimento-stuffed olives.
Toss
together
with
mayonnaise blended with chili sauce.
Mix well and spread mixture in split frankfurter rolls.	Wrap
each in aluminum foil, twisting the ends securely.
Bake 10	minutes
in 400° oven until rolls are hot. These can be
made	ahead,	kept
in
refrigerator,
then
heated at serving time.

title: wild rice with mushrooms
directions: Steam or cook rice according to package directions.
Saute green onions and mushrooms in oil.
Combine the cooked rice.
Stir in margarine and pepper.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; cut into bite size pieces and layer in casserole dish.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing; set aside.
Dice onion and celery; saute in butter.
Stir in soup, wine and mayonnaise until smooth.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Wash, trim and dry broccoli.
In saucepan, cook broccoli in butter until soft.
Blend in flour and simmer until smooth and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Add milk, chicken broth, salt, pepper, lemon juice, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Whirl in blender until smooth.
Stir in cream and Velveeta cheese; heat until hot and cheese is melted.
Stir constantly.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour.
Brown meat in shortening; drain off excess fat.
Place in Dutch oven.
Put the following in a skillet and cook until bacon is crisp: bacon, garlic, carrots, onions and parsley.
Add to meat in Dutch oven.
Add bay leaves, thyme, allspice and wine to meat with enough water to cover meat.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Brown 2 pounds small onions in shortening and cook, covered, until done.
Add to meat and serve.
Garnish with sauteed mushrooms.

title: sauerkraut soup("kapusniak")
directions: Cook pork shanks in water in a 5-quart kettle for 20 minutes. Skim off foam.
Add onion, bay leaf, peppercorns and parsley. Cook about 45 minutes or until the meat is tender.
Remove meat from broth.
Strain broth; return to kettle.
Remove meat from bone; discard bone and skin.
Dice meat.
Rinse sauerkraut with cold water.
Drain.
Add diced meat, drained kraut, beef broth and if desired bacon and raisins to kettle.
Simmer 1 hour.
Mix lard and flour to a smooth paste; stir into simmering soup.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Mix in salt and pepper. Serve with plain boiled potato dumplings if desired.

title: one bowl fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chocolate with milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small saucepan, melt butter in water over medium-low heat.
Add flour and salt, stirring until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs and beat vigorously until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove puffs, cool and split.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Cook together the cheese, milk and nutmeg until cheese is melted.
Add spinach and half of the bacon and lemon juice.
Top with remaining bacon bits.
Serve with vegetables and crackers.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Place a slice of ham in each section of a muffin tin. Sprinkle cheese in each, making a well.
Drizzle cream in each and then put an egg in each section.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey oriental
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery and onions in oil in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Add turkey, tomato sauce, bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Blend water and cornstarch.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cake or pudding
directions: Take 1 pound each of diced potatoes, cauliflower, swedes and carrots, three or four spring onions, if possible one teaspoonful of vegetable extract and one tablespoonful of oatmeal.
Cook all together for 10 minutes, with just enough water to cover.
Stir occasionally to prevent the mixture from sticking.
Allow to cool; put into a pie dish and sprinkle with chopped parsley and cover with a crust of potatoes or wholemeal pastry.
Bake in a moderate oven until the pastry is nicely brown and serve hot with a brown gravy.
(GR)

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Take 1 cup of self-rising flour and a spoon of butter; stir until crumbly.
Add the sweet milk; stir.
Pat down.
Cut biscuits.
Make a small hole in the middle; dip down in butter, then in cinnamon-sugar.
Twist and bake at 375° until done.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature. Mix all ingredients together. Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecan nuts.

title: cucumber and onions
directions: Using equal amounts of sliced cucumbers, onion and green pepper rings, mix and marinate in vinegar, water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well and allow to set at least 24 hours.
Extra good with green beans.

title: bits and pieces salad
directions: Prepare salad greens and top with the remaining ingredients. Toss with you favorite salad dressing and croutons.
Enjoy!!

title: lemon-glazed chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place skin side down in a shallow baking dish.
Mix concentrate with soy sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400°, turning once and basting occasionally, 40 minutes or until chicken is browned and fork-tender.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat yolks with shortening and margarine at high speed.
Add sugar, then extracts.
At low speed, beat in flour (in 1/4's) with milk (in 1/3's). Add coconut, beat.
Beat egg whites, fold into batter.
Pour into greased 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: fruit nectar salad
directions: Heat apricot nectar and water to boiling; pour over orange gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Drain and reserve pineapple; measure syrup (there should be 1 cup).
Add syrup to orange gelatin mixture; chill until syrupy.
Drain apricots.
Fold crushed pineapple and apricots into chilled, syrupy gelatin.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart mold; chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese into pieces.
In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs, flour and cheese pieces.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Arrange remaining cheese on top.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Use 1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cups hot water.
Top with Cool Whip or marshmallows.
Should make 96 cups.
Keeps well in dry container.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, sugar, pineapple juice in large container and mix until sugar is dissolved.
Freeze to slush.
To serve, pour mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Stir well. Makes 32 punch cup servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oil in an iron skillet until hot.
Mix remaining ingredients except the cheese.
Pour half the batter in iron skillet.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top of batter.
Pour remainder of batter on top of cheese.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese in middle of batter.
If sprinkled on edges cheese will burn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in 2-quart saucepan. Heat until butter melts at medium heat, then cook 3 minutes. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop from tablespoon on waxed paper.
Cool.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: pineapple-coconut
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour and water alternately.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 3 layer pans.
Between each layer and on top, use pineapple and juice, coconut and frosting.

title: dill sauce
directions: In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Stir in broth, salt and dill.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Excellent over cooked shrimp with a side of noodles or rice.
Also good on Danish/Swedish meatballs.

title: cheesy chicken stuffing bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour stuffing into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Add cheese, chicken and pepper.
In a separate bowl, gradually stir milk into flour.
Stir in eggs.
Pour over stuffing mixture.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until golden brown.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Mix the Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, basil, parsley and eggs. Layer, beginning with noodles and 1/2 mixture. Repeat. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna mousse(preparation time:  20 minutes)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat tomato soup and add gelatin. Let cool and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: easy french onion rice
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add rice and mix together.
Add soup, water, and mushrooms with juice.
Pepper to taste.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Stir again. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 20 mins. or until liquid is absorbed.

title: orange roughy almandine
directions: Cut fillets in serving pieces; arrange in a 10 x 6-inch microwave baking dish.
Sprinkle parsley, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes, rotating dish once.
Set aside, covered.
Combine almonds and margarine in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Transfer fish to platter; pour almonds over fish.
Serves 6 and has only 140 calories per serving.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: lo-cal chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam; press graham cracker crumbs into pan.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Stir and heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Set aside.
Put in blender the remaining cold water, cottage cheese, butter extract, chocolate milk beverage and artificial sweetener.
Process until smooth. Add gelatin and blend.
Drop in the ice until blender is full; blend.
Pour into crust and add whipped topping.

title: quick fruit scramble
directions: Combine apples, bananas, grapes and pineapple in a bowl.
Mix applesauce, pineapple juice concentrate and pecans in a bowl.
Pour over fruit, mixing well.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Add pudding to Cool Whip and mix.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a very large casserole.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients, shortening and yeast mixture together; knead on floured board for few minutes.
Cover in a bowl and let rise; pinch off as wanted for biscuits.
This will keep in icebox for several days.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: grandmother's homemade potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes and onions together until well done.
Add the cream, butter, salt and pepper. Cook for 1/2 hour on medium heat.

title: macadamia nut crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine eggs, banana, butter, fruit spread and vanilla in a medium bowl.
Add flour, coconut, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop a tablespoon of dough 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks. Store in tightly covered container.

title: parsnip casserole
directions: Cook parsnips until almost done in water to almost cover parsnips.
Remove parsnips with a slotted spoon and put in greased casserole.
To the parsnip water, add salt and pepper and cut chunks of cheese in simmering water.
Stir until melted; pour over parsnips.
Crumble cracker crumbs or potato chips on top.
Put in 375° oven until top is nicely browned.

title: scalloped potatoes 'n franks
directions: Place ham on a broiler pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Make sure all lumps in sweet potatoes are mashed out.
Add all ingredients and and pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted into the filling 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve with seasoned whipped cream, if desired.

title: german potato pancakes (kartoffelpuffer)
directions: Peel and shred (or grate) potatoes and onion.
Place them in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, beat the egg.
Gradually add the flour, salt, parsley and nutmeg, beating with a wire whisk.
Pour the mixture over the shredded potatoes and onion, stirring to combine.

title: josephines
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
While warm, right out of oven, roll gently in flat pan with sifted powdered sugar until it equals 2-inch ball.
Set aside to cool.
Enjoy!!
Melts in your mouth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 of stuffing mix in melted margarine.
Put chicken over this.
Add onion.
Pour mushroom soup over this.
Add 3 cups of chicken broth over this. Add remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered. Remove cover and brown.

title: kwakuitl potato salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, honey and celery seed.
Pour over steamed ferns and allow to stand 3 hours.
Combine potatoes, onion, eggs and celery.
Mix together into potato mixture and blend gently.
Season to taste.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 3 cups of berries in pie shell. Combine remaining berries and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add sugar and cornstarch. Cook till thick and clear. Stir in lemon
juice. Pour over berries in pie shell. Chill several hours. Serve with whipped cream.

title: vidalia onion cake
directions: Mix baking soda with tomato soup; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add cloves and nutmeg to flour; sift together.
Combine soup mixture and flour.
Add onions, nuts and raisins (drained).
Bake at 325° in greased and floured or otherwise prepared tube pan or Bundt pan for about an hour or until done with toothpick test.
Remove from pan as soon as heat from pan will allow; cool upside down.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Wash and drain a batch of firm green beans.
Remove ends and strings.
Use a large darning needle with heavy white thread and thread through the pod near the middle of each bean, pushing them along about 1/4-inch apart.
Hang up the strings of beans in warm, well ventilated place to dry.
They will shrivel and turn greenish gray.

title: sausage souffle(for brunch)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add sausage last.
Refrigerate overnight (approximately 12 hours).
Bake 60 minutes at 350° in a casserole dish.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix hamburger, liquid, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper. Flatten meat
mixture
in
a
square
pan and cover with waxed paper.
Refrigerate
for
1 hour.
Cut meat into serving size. Turn in
flour
and
place	pieces in a baking pan.
Pour soup over the
meat.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Time of preparation: 2 hours.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Combine salt and pepper. Sprinkle over chicken. Brown slowly in butter.
Remove from pan.
Cook onion until tender. Place onion to side. Add chicken.
Add mushrooms and tarragon. Sprinkle onion over. Add water and cover.
Simmer until chicken is done, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chipped beef gravy
directions: In large frying pan melt butter.
Add flour.
Stir in chipped beef and saute a little.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Add water and bring to a second boil.
Cook until desired consistency. Serve over toast.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook pie shell; cook sugar, egg yolks, milk and salt until thickens, then add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with stiffly beaten egg whites, sweetened to taste.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the pudding as directed, then place in refrigerator to chill.
Break the cake into little bite size pieces.
Mix the Cool Whip with the pudding and fold into cake pieces.
Pour into a long dish and top with strawberries.

title: cheese fruit whip
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cottage cheese to soften.
Stir in and let stand a few minutes. Stir again to dissolve gelatin.
Fold in whipped topping and fruits.
Cover and refrigerate until time to serve. Divide into 6 dessert dishes. Serves 6. Contains 125 calories.

title: sheet cake
directions: Combine oleo, cocoa and water in a pan.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add sugar, flour, soda and salt, which have been stirred together.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into a greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: For dressing, combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread on each slice of bread.
Top with kraut, corned beef and cheese.
Put together as a sandwich; butter outsides of each sandwich.
Brown on both sides on buttered skillet until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: prickly pear jelly
directions: Bring first four ingredients, juice, water, lemon juice and commercial jell to a rapid boil.
Add sugar all at once and return to a rapid boil again.
Although most jelly recipes say boil hard for 1 minute, she boils hers 10 minutes.
Stir once or twice during the boiling.
Skim foam off top.
Pour into hot sterilized jars. Seal with paraffin.

title: spinach and cheese quiche
directions: Mix flour and salt in large bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until coarse crumbs form.
Add water, tossing with fork, until dough forms.
Press into a firm ball.
Wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-sour cream salad
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water; let congeal slightly.
Mix cranberry sauce, celery, nuts and sour cream.
Stir into gelatin mix.
Pour into molds and refrigerate. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Saute thinly sliced boneless chicken breast in small amount of peanut oil (add a little water).
Add sliced water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, soy sauce, sprinkle of garlic powder and sugar. Heat thoroughly.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In
a large bowl, beat egg yolks well.
Stir in milk, vanilla and strawberries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour mixture in 2-quart container and freeze until firm.

title: pecan corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl; set aside. Mix together half and half, butter and eggs in another bowl. Stir liquid mixture and pecans into cornmeal mixture until just combined. Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted into middle of loaf comes out clean. Cool in pan on cooling rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, butter and pecans, then press into the bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash until just tender.
Drain well.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients to the eggs. Pour into buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter or top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great dish to share at a cook out!

title: pizza loaf
directions: Mix everything together except cheese.
Divide meat in thirds. Press one layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle with cheese, then meat, then cheese on top again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Prepare lemon jello in glass dish using 1 cup of hot water and less than 1/2 cup of cold water. Stir until dissolved.
Add carrots, nuts, pineapple with juice and raisins. Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until congealed.

title: jalapeno ketchup
directions: Chop onion and peppers very fine.
Stir all together and simmer about 1 1/2 hours. Seal in ketchup bottles.

title: sand tarts
directions: Add flour to stiffen.
Makes 7 to 8 cups.
Roll out thin.
Cut into shapes.
Decorate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: deviled cheese balls
directions: Blend cream cheese and deviled ham; chill.
Place pineapple tidbits on paper towels to drain; cut each piece in half crosswise.
Roll spoonful of cheese mixture around each pineapple piece to form 1-inch ball; chill.
Roll balls in chopped parsley or chives.
Chill.
Serve on toothpicks.
Yields 30 servings.

title: baked apples with sausage stuffing
directions: Cut a slice from each apple top.
Scoop out the cores and pulp, leaving shells about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut the pulp from the cores and combine with sausage.
Sprinkle apple shells with salt and sugar.
Fill shells heaping full of sausage.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in margarine.
Brown ground beef in another pan.
Combine tomato sauce, onion and bell pepper. Salt and sugar (if needed).
Add raw rice; simmer a few minutes. Add ground beef and bring to a rolling boil.
Lower heat and cook until rice is tender.
Fluff with fork and add shredded cheese. Cover a few minutes and let cheese melt.

title: pascha
directions: Make a well in pan of flour; add eggs, butter, milk and yeast. Knead until dough is mixed. Remove dough from pan; clean pan with shortening. Put dough back into pan and knead a few times. Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 2 hours.

title: lipton california dip
directions: In small bowl, blend all ingredients; chill.
Makes about 2 cups dip.
For a creamier dip, add more sour cream.

title: lemon bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs with milk 1/2 hour.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Stir in the milk mixture.
Pour into a 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Place the dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: In a deep bowl, salt and stack slices of eggplant. Place plate on top and let set for an hour or so. Then drain and rinse and dice. Cook in boiling water for 6 to 7 minutes. Drain. Meanwhile, stir milk into soup; blend in egg. Add drained eggplant, onion and stuffing. Toss to mix. Turn into greased baking dish 10 x 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into buttered dish and spread.
Add cherry pie filling and spread.
Sift cake mix over fruit as evenly as possible.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Distribute butter slices over mixture and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve the cake hot with ice cream or cold with whipped topping or just plain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and pepper until tender.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in greased casserole.
Put corn flakes, cracker crumbs or bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: robert's hot dogs
directions: Slice wieners down the middle, but not all the way. Slice cheese into several pieces and stuff the cheese inside the wieners. Wrap the bacon around the wiener. Line a cookie sheet pan with aluminum foil. Put the wieners on the pan and bake for 30 minutes or until the bacon gets done, in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: date roll-ups-cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in other ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick with confectioners sugar on the board.
Cut with knife into 1 x 3-inch pieces.
Put date in center and roll.
Place folded side on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
When serving, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: yankee red flannel hash
directions: Lightly toss beef, potatoes, beets and onion together.
Add milk, salt and tabasco.
Season to taste with more salt and pepper if needed.
Melt 3/4 tablespoons fat in skillet,
spread hash evenly over bottom. Cook over medium heat until underneath side is brown and crusty.
Makes 4 servings.
Author unknown.

title: grits dressing(serves 10)
directions: Heat a well-greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet in a 325° oven 5 minutes or until hot.
Combine grits, flour, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture. Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Remove skillet from oven and pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm in center, but not browned.
Cool and crumble.
Combine crumbled bread, onion and remaining ingredients; pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until firm. Yields 10 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli rice casserole
directions: Simmer onions and mushrooms in a large skillet with oleo until tender.
Stir in rice, chicken, broccoli and soup.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat. Add flour and soda; beat again.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake in 15 x 10-inch pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake. Let cool before cutting.

title: crock-pot hamburger casserole
directions: Place layers of vegetables in the order given in greased crock-pot.
Season each with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned hamburger on top of the celery.
Mix the tomato soup with the water and pour into the crock-pot.
Cover and set on low for 6 to 8 hours.
(High for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.)

title: chicken liver pate with bacon
directions: Simmer livers in broth with onions until livers are tender, about 15 minutes.
Let cool in broth.
Drain and reserve broth. Put 1/4 cup of broth, livers, onions and remaining ingredients into a blender or food processor.
Cover and run on high speed until smooth.
Refrigerate in a covered container at least 24 hours to blend flavors.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add sugar and salt.
Blend in flour.
Knead until smooth.
Roll into strips and shape pretzels (any shape you would like them in).
Place on foiled cookie sheet. Brush pretzels with beaten egg and sprinkle on kosher salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes!

title: rohlicky(cookies)
directions: Cut butter into flour as with pie crust.
Blend the egg yolk with sour cream and add to flour.
Blend well.
Form into ball and cover with wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours. Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part into a 12-inch circle. Cut into 16 wedges.

title: cola barbecue chicken
directions: Flour pieces as if to fry but place in greased casserole dish (covered).
Salt and pepper.
Mix together catsup and Coke.
Pour mixture over all pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (uncovered last 10 minutes to crisp).

title: favorite rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator at least 4 hours (works good to leave it overnight).
Put apart and place in muffin tins (will be sticky).
Let raise at least 3 hours in muffin tins.
Cover with a light cloth to raise.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Wash cauliflower and separate into flowerets, slicing larger ones into bite size pieces.
Wash broccoli; trim large leaves from stalk.
Cut flowerets into bite size pieces.
Cut skin and tough end section from stalks; slice remainder into bite size pieces. In a large bowl, combine broccoli and cauliflower with onion rings and mushrooms.
Combine mayonnaise, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to make dressing.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly. Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with crumbled bacon. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add soup, chicken, pepper, paprika and curry powder.
Mix well.
Place alternate layers of noodle mixture and cheeses in a casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, cornmeal, vanilla, butter and vinegar; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes, then stir gently.
(Do let this stand for 10 minutes and then stir; it will separate if you do not.)
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put spatini or tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodles little italy
directions: Cook
macaroni	in 2-quarts water; drain and set aside. In
a saucepan, combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, garlic salt, oregano
and
pepperoni (reserve 6 or 7 slices for garnish). Simmer
mixture
for
minutes.	In a large bowl or pan, combine
sauce
and
macaroni;
mix well.
Place 1/2 the mixture in	a
greased 2-quart casserole dish and fold in 1/2 the shredded
cheese.
Put
rest
of mixture in casserole and fold
in remaining cheese.	Reserve enough cheese to sprinkle on
top
of casserole.	Garnish top with pepperoni slices and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until casserole is fully heated and cheese is all melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple tart(sugar-free dessert)
directions: Combine apples, Splenda, flour and cinnamon.
Roll out pie crust to pizza-size and place on cookie sheet.
Place apple mixture in center and pat with butter.
Fold crust edges over apple mixture until enclosed.
Brush crust with egg white.
Bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add eggs one at a time beating well after each.
Add flour, whipping cream, vanilla and lemon and beat well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300 degrees.
Place in cold oven.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container.
For each serving, use 1 teaspoon per cup of boiling water and stir until dissolved.

title: baked beans
directions: Add 6 cups cold water to beans; bring to boil, then simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover tightly and let stand 1 hour. Add salt pork; let boil, then simmer 1 hour.
Drain; keep juice. Take out salt pork to taste.
Mix in saucepan, tomato sauce, paste, catsup, brown sugar, mustard, molasses, honey and onion. Mix with beans.
Place bacon in baking dish, then pour in bean mix.
Add 3 or 4 tablespoons bean water.
Cover with foil with 1 air hole.
Bake at 275° for 5 to 6 hours.
After 2 1/2 hours, check and add bean water.

title: lollie's upside down cake
directions: Place 1 cup brown sugar and 3 Tbsp. butter in cast iron Dutch oven and simmer for 10 minutes.
Lay rings of pineapple in skillet and add a cherry in each ring.
Over this, pour remaining brown sugar.
Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs.
Then add milk slowly.
Pour this over pineapple rings.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to batter a little at a time, along with vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together with beater.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: golden onion chicken and rice
directions: Bring water to boil in a large deep skillet.
Stir in the onion soup and chicken thighs.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rice and mixed vegetables.
Cover again and cook 20 minutes or until the rice is tender, the liquid is absorbed and the chicken is no longer pink near the bone.

title: more and more
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Drain.
Saute onions until soft. Add meat.
Cook until brown; add green pepper, corn, chili powder and salt.
Combine with noodles and top with cheese in a 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good frozen in meal size containers.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine
beef
and onions in a skillet.
Cook until the meat is lightly brown.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, ketchup and tomato soup.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole
dish.
Cut
the
cheese
into strips and sprinkle
over the meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix can of fruit cocktail with mandarin oranges. Add strawberries.
Mix and chill.

title: apple cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Grease and flour baking pan.
Cream eggs and sugar together. Add oil, vanilla, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and apples.
Blend well.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Frost when cool with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix together all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Scrape bowl often.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: beef fantastic
directions: Blend all the cans of soup (do not add any water).
Mix in stew meat cubes (do not thaw stew meat; better if it's frozen). Put in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours on low.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Great for working parents!

title: cherry no-dough cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch cake pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk in a large bowl.
Pour batter in 9-inch buttered pan.
Spoon cherries into the center of batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed mushroom caps with crab meat
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, garlic and parsley in butter for 10 minutes; cool.
Combine bread crumbs, cream, raw and cooked eggs, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, Tabasco sauce, salt and crab meat with vegetables.
Stuff cleaned and stemmed mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a covered dish.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of mushrooms and cover. Serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add corn, soups, pimento, salt, pepper, noodles and sour cream.
Mix well.
Put in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together the flour and pecans. Combine the corn syrup, butter and sugar in a saucepan over moderate heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove the pan from heat.
Gradually add the flour and nut mixture to the hot mixture.
Cool slightly.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Glaze while cake is hot.

title: hot fudge sunday cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together, then mix brown sugar and cocoa together and sprinkle on top.
Pour hot water over and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cake will come to top with chocolate sauce on bottom.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, salt, cocoa and milk for 3 minutes.
Then add Mother's Oats and nutmeats.
Beat until cool.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
These are no bake cookies.

title: irene's prize pickled shrimp
directions: Cover shrimp with boiling water and add celery tops, mixed pickling spices and 3 1/2 teaspoons salt. Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Drain and cool with cool water. Peel and devein shrimp under cold water. Layer shrimp and onions. Mix the bay leaves, salad oil, white vinegar, celery seed, salt and Tabasco and pour over shrimp and onions. Marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix lemon jello with hot water.
Add sugar.
Mix and add to jello mixture the chilled Milnot.
Put half of graham crackers on bottom and half on top.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add enough water to make paste.
Beat in egg yolks well.
Heat remaining water and add with butter and salt.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries.
Chill until firm.
Whip whipping cream.
Add to Jell-O.
Beat with mixer.
Refrigerate.

title: whipped sweet potato bake
directions: Beat sweet potatoes, margarine, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until sweet potatoes are hot and marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: lemon velvet ice cream
directions: Squeeze juice and pulp from oranges and lemons; stir in sugar. Add milk.
Pour into freezer container and freeze.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Can add extra M&M's on top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground sirloin.
Strain off fat and add garlic salt.
Add picante sauce.
Reduce heat.
Cover 20 minutes until liquid absorbs into meat.
Heat shells.
Add lettuce to cover bottom.
Add meat to cover lettuce.
Top with taco cheese.
Add tomatoes, black olives and sliced avocados.
Put a dab of sour cream on top.

title: baked shrimp with feta cheese
directions: In a large nonstick saucepan, heat the oil and saute the onion over medium heat for 7 to 8 minutes or until soft and lightly golden, stirring often.
Add the tomatoes, parsley, dill, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat the oven to 375°.
Generously spray a shallow ovenproof dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Place the shrimp in the bottom of the prepared dish.
Pour the cooked sauce over and crumble the Feta cheese on top.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the shrimp are tender and the Feta cheese begins to melt slightly.
Serve the shrimp hot.
Serves 4.

title: artichoke adventure dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve warm with crackers, chips, etc.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gingered almonds
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place almonds and butter in shallow baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle salt and ginger over nuts and toss. Serve warm.

title: chili
directions: Blend onions in blender until soupy.
Brown onions in bacon drippings for 15 minutes.
Add hamburger, stirring until done; drain grease, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat until thick.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Pour melted margarine over Ritz cracker crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan to make crust.
Beat ice cream, milk and pudding about 10 minutes.
Pour onto crust.
Refrigerate for 3 or 4 hours.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle the 1/4 cup reserved crumbs on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat in skillet until garlic is lightly browned 1/2 cup olive oil and 2 garlic cloves, sliced thin.
Meanwhile coat with flour 1 frying chicken.
Place skin side down in skillet with oil and brown.
While chicken is browning, combine 3 1/2 cups tomatoes (sieved), 1 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon oregano and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Slowly add tomato mixture to browned chicken with 1 teaspoon chopped parsley.
Cook slowly 25 to 30 minutes or until thickest pieces of chicken are tender when pierced with fork.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and mince.
Mix stems, cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, butter, garlic, and onion.
Fill mushrooms with mixture, pressing in firmly.
Grease (or spray with Pam) a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place mushrooms facing upwards. Pour remaining oil over mushrooms.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: In large skillet, brown pork on all sides in shortening. Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice, water, vinegar and soy sauce.
Remove browned meat from skillet.
Blend cornstarch mixture into pan drippings.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add meat to sauce and cook, covered, over low heat until meat is tender (about 45 minutes).
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 3 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.
Pass additional soy sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Put everything but meat into blender and mix well.
Pour over meat and thoroughly mix.
Shape into small 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls. Fry gently to brown.
Cover and simmer with small amount of water after meatballs well browned.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Can make gravy from drippings or small can mushroom sauce works well.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Cut up broccoli, carrots and cauliflower.
Mix rest of ingredients well and pour over slaw; crumble remaining chips and add on top of slaw.

title: poppy seed fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Reserve 1 tablespoon pineapple juice.
Cut strawberries and apple,
Combine fruit in a bowl.
Mix yogurt, poppy seed and reserved pineapple juice.
Arrange fruit in 6 serving bowls.
Drizzle dressing over fruit.

title: crunchy chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to main ingredients.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and noodles.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook all meat first.
Then add all other ingredients.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients. Grease pan; bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: yeast rolls(feather light)
directions: Put all ingredients except yeast in mixing bowl; reserve 1 cup of flour (use this to roll out rolls).
Beat smooth; add yeast mixture.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Dump roll dough out over 1 cup of flour and knead smooth.
Roll out rolls 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on greased pan and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Brush rolls with melted butter as soon as they come out of the oven.

title: turtle fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in heavy saucepan (2 1/2 to 3-quart size).

Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 234° or soft ball stage, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; add chocolate and stir until well blended.
