Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: savory green beans
directions: Wash beans and trim ends; remove strings.
Cut in half crosswise.
Using an iron skillet, heat oil and add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender; discard garlic.
Add beans, boiling water and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until beans are tender.

title: summer pizza
directions: Cream
mayonnaise, cream
cheese and Hidden Valley
and spread on crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables and cheese.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and butter; stir in milk, vanilla and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes until hot and thick.
If mixture becomes too thick, add 1 tablespoon hot water to make desired consistency.
Good over vanilla ice cream, over angel food or pound cake.
Dip cookies in.
Yummy.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter and cheese; add sugar and cream well; add vanilla.
Slowly mix the flour into the cream mixture.
Fill cookie press with mixture.
Using the star plate, form cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Hold press semi-horizontal and form wreaths by moving press in a circular motion.
Gently push ends of dough together to form wreath shape. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Slice berries; put in pie crust.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and Sprite and dash of salt until mixture thickens.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Pour over berries and chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: goulash
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch cubes.
Brown in hot fat.
Add the finely chopped onion and saute together a little longer.
Pour in the boiling water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and braise gently until done.
Season to taste with paprika and salt.
Thicken with cornstarch, blended with water.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut butter into coarse crumbs with a fork; stir into a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board and knead 10 times until smooth.
Roll out on board to a square to fit a 9 x 12-inch pan, or place on cookie sheet.
Cut dough into 12 portions.
Do not separate.
Leave in square.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef with onion and drain. Add beans and soup.
Add water, vinegar, chili powder and flour. Stir mixture 3 to 4 times. Cover and simmer on low heat 30 to 45 minutes until done. Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine 1st seven ingredients and mix gently.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cornwell cheese squares
directions: Melt cream cheese, sharp cheese and butter in double boiler. Fold in egg whites.
Remove crust from bread.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Dip bread cubes in warm cheese.
Put on wax lined cookie sheet.
Freeze.
When frozen put in plastic bag or container.
When ready to serve, pop in oven for 10 minutes at 400°.
Good appetizer to have on hand for unexpected occasions.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mash with milk and butter.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes, or until heated through.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Add Jell-O, sugar and cornstarch to boiling water.
Cook until clear.
Cool slightly. Then add one pint strawberries.
Let stand until cold and begins to gel.
Pour into a baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Cook bacon until crisp in skillet over medium fire.
Remove and crumble.
Reserving drippings.
Add corn, sugar, milk, salt and pepper to reserved drippings.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine cream and flour in jar; shake until blended.
Stir into corn mixture.
Add margarine; cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly. Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sondra's easy cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
When cake is cool, poke holes with wooden spoon handle in cake.
Pour milk in holes and over top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Squeeze out excess oil before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popped corn into large baking pan. Keep warm in 200° oven.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Combine juice of pineapple with pudding.
When thickened, add fruits.
Add Tang last.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Mix as listed and bring to full boil.
Cool and refrigerate.
Pour over fresh fruit.

title: santa's whiskers cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla. Stir in cherries and nuts.
Form in two rolls 2-inches in diameter.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill for several hours. Slice 1/4-inch thick; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together sugars, butter and oil.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients; mix well.
Add zucchini; stir until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix flour, garlic, oregano, eggs and milk.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle hamburger on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add desired sauce and toppings; bake another 15 minutes.

title: rabbit stew
directions: Disjoint the rabbit.
Cover and soak overnight in equal parts of water and vinegar. Drain well, then roll in flour and fry rabbit in hot bacon fat or butter.
Place rabbit in a casserole or pan. To 1/3 cup drippings, add 4 tablespoons flour, stirring until it bubbles.

Pour in 2 cups of water and cook until mixture thickens. Salt to taste, then pour in 1 cup tart red jelly and 1 tablespoon mixed pickling spices. Pour this gravy mixture over the rabbit. If necessary, add more water.
Meat should be covered. Close casserole tightly and cook for 1 hour or more. Serve with noodles or brown rice.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs into approximately 1/2 inch pieces.
Combine all other ingredients into saucepan.
Stir in sliced hot dogs. Simmer until sauce is thick (this takes quite a while).
Serve in slow cooker on lowest heat to keep them warm.
Have toothpicks near to serve with.
Makes 8 servings.

title: walnut and wild rice chicken salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Cool. In a large bowl, combine yogurt, mayo, green onions, olive oil, lemon peel, salt, lemon juice and pepper. Stir in rice, chicken and walnuts. Refrigerate until serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients as listed in glass 9 x 12-inch dish. Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Carefully spread mayonnaise mixture over lettuce.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Coat steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat, stirring several times.
Add sliced onions to steak.
Cook until onions are clear, but not brown.
Reduce heat to low; drain off fat.

title: yummy cheese dip
directions: In a crock-pot combine cheese block, tomatoes, chili and picante sauce.
Turn to high heat until cheese is melted.
Stir and turn down to low heat.
Stir occasionally to keep from burning. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Refrigerate until cool. Serve with apple wedges as a dip.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onions and drain excess fat.
Add drained can of kidney beans with other ingredients.
Bring to a boil then simmer on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: company breakfast
directions: Mix together in greased 9X13 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: creamy orange custard
directions: Combine milk, vanilla and orange zest in a microwave-safe 4 cup glass measure.
Place on microwave turntable.
Microwave uncovered at 100% power for 2 minutes.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix nuts, raisins, persimmons, sugar, eggs and oil and set aside.

title: delicious frozen corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in containers of your choice.

title: citrus sherbet ring
directions: Peel and section grapefruit.
Reserve juices.
Set aside. Add enough water to reserved juice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add gelatin.
Cook and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in sherbet.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in grapefruit sections and pecans.
Turn into 3-cup ring mold.
Chill until firmly set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind all fruits and nuts together.
Mix sugar, hot water and jello.
Stir fruit and nut mixture into jello mixture.
Add enough food coloring to give salad a bright color.
Chill until firm.

title: sister robbie's 2-9 coconut pies
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks, milk and vanilla. Blend well.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and blend; add vanilla. Pour in shell.

title: cinnamon poached peaches
directions: In a 2-quart nonmetal casserole combine the peach or apple halves, apple juice, honey, stick cinnamon and vanilla.
In the microwave oven cook, covered on High for 1 to 4 minutes, or until fruit is tender, giving dish a half turn once during cooking and spooning juice over fruit.
Transfer fruit to dessert dishes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt (but not necessary).
Blend soup and wine.
Add mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Uncover the last 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter and sprinkle with paprika.
Pour sauce into pan; add sour cream.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve over chicken and rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Bring fruit and sugar to boil; cook for 15 minutes.
Add jello; cook for 8 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: catfish sauce piquante
directions: Make a light colored roux (white sauce with oil and flour). Add onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery to roux.
Cook slightly.
Stir in 1 cup of water and 1 cup of tomato sauce. Cook, covered, for 1 hour on low heat.
Add fish, then cook for 45 minutes.
Season according to taste.
Add onion tops and parsley when cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake as directed in 11 x 15-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kentucky delight
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in bite size pieces.
Put into dish.
Mix melted margarine, cream cheese, and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip until creamy.
Spread half of mixture over cake, sprinkle half of candy bars over for topping.
Repeat to make two layers.
Can be made several days ahead and stored in refrigerator.

title: sue's special sauce
directions: Bring to boil, simmer 5 minutes.
Stir.

title: banana-date cookies
directions: Mash bananas, leaving some pieces.
Add chopped dates and honey.
Beat with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Let stand a few minutes for oatmeal to absorb moisture. Drop from spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes or until nicely browned.
Loosen with spatula and let cool on cookie sheet.

title: easy oven pork chops
directions: Melt butter in pan in oven.
Make crumb mixture, using cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix together egg and milk.
Coat chops with crumbs, dip in egg mixture and then in crumbs again.
Place chops in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes on one side.
Turn.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: stacked quesadillas
directions: Stir green chillies into cream cheese.
Stack tortillas on a 10-inch plate, spreading each with about 1/3 cup cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 12 appetizers.
Contains 75 calories per serving.

title: applesauce cake loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg, beating well.	Add nuts and raisins.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.	Bake at 350° for 75 minutes in greased loaf pan.

title: southwestern rice salad
directions: Combine oil, sour cream, lime juice, salt, cumin, sugar and red pepper.
Stir or shake well.
Immediately combine with rice in medium bowl.
Add olives, corn, bell pepper, tomato, green onions, avocado, cilantro and jalapeno peppers; toss gently to mix. Season with salt and black pepper.
Serve salad chilled or at room temperature.
Makes 4 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: grandma's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple confetti cake
directions: Place package of cake mix in a bowl. Add can of pineapple including the juice. Pour into a ungreased cake pan. Bake at 350 degrees for
approx. 35-45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine vegetables; salt and pepper real good.
Mash egg yolks with fork; add mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Stir and spread over peeled, cut up chunked vegetables and mix.
Chill.

title: blitz torte(a dessert)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add the four egg yolks all at once.
Sift baking powder and flour and add alternately with the milk to egg and butter mixture.
Pour batter into two 10-inch cake pans, which have been well-greased (can use 9-inch pans, but cake will be thicker).
Beat four egg whites until stiff and add granulated sugar, a little at a time.
Spread this meringue over batter in the cake pans.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake in 350° oven.
Place pans on center rack for 35 minutes until meringue is a lovely beige color.

title: mary ann's chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, combine baking chocolate, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and cool.
Beat eggs; add to chocolate mixture.
Add flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly (batter will be thin).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: spicy chicken wings(makes about 20 appetizers)
directions: In small shallow dish, combine cracker crumbs and chili powder; set aside.
Place 3/4 cup salsa in shallow bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in salsa; roll in cracker mixture.
Place on greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown, turning after 15 minutes.
Serve hot with remaining salsa.

title: garlic sauce
directions: Blend ingredients.
Use a pasta sauce or basting sauce.

title: tuna zucchini cakes
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add other ingredients and combine well.
Shape into six 1/2-inch thick patties.
Coat patties with bread crumbs.
Heat oil in skillet and cook patties on each side until golden (approximately 3 minutes).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Do not cool.
Put in casserole dish and add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Place in microwave until cheese melts.

title: june's baked beans
directions: Place baked beans in casserole. Combine remaining ingredients and mix into beans.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix cocoa, flour and sugar with eggs.
Add milk and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour in pie shell.

title: venison and tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground venison into ungreased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Cover with broccoli and cheese soup, undiluted.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and brown
ground
chuck,
onion
and
pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and place in 350° oven for 30 or 35 minutes.
(May also be cooked in crock-pot.)

title: toffee bars
directions: Cram the butter and add sugar and egg yolk.
Mix well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Spread in a 10 x 14-inch ungreased shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place the candy bar which has been broken into small pieces on top of this and spread as it melts.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut while warm.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: fluffy hamburger meat balls
directions: Beat egg yolks about one minute.
Add beaten yolks to ground beef along with chopped onion, parsley, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Mix well and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to meat mixture and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons into hot grease and fry until brown.

title: dip for strawberries
directions: Mix well together.
Dip strawberries in it.

title: basic art dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Knead 10 minutes. Model as with any clay. Bake at 300° until hard or air dry for a few days.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, dice and boil until tender.
Drain.
Cream like making cream potatoes.
Add margarine and just enough milk to keep them from being stiff.
Add mustard and dressing to taste.
I use about 2/3 cup of mustard and not quite as much salad dressing.
Add onions to taste (about 1/2 cup).
Chop 4 eggs in potatoes.
Mix. Put 1 egg across top (sliced).
Add salt and pepper.

title: potato kish
directions: Add 1 egg, 1 cup flour and dash of salt to amount of shredded potatoes for 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes in a pie plate sprayed with no-stick spray.
Remove from oven and add onion, chopped ham and broccoli.
Beat 3 eggs and light cream together.
Add dash of salt, pepper and nutmeg; pour over onion, ham and broccoli.
Add grated cheese and paprika on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: korean barbecue
directions: Pour soy sauce, sugar and water into the large bowl and stir until sugar dissolves.
Add chopped green onion, chopped garlic and black pepper.
Marinate each slice and gently pat them.
Add sesami oil to the marinated meat.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour. Grill or broil from heat, turning once, for 10 to 15 minutes or until completely cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together the eggs, oil and corn bread mix.
Stir in the cheese, corn and onion.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake about 45 minutes at 400°.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add margarine; cool. Add eggs, flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can double batch for freezing.

title: phyllis' corn dish
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese together.
Mix corn and green chilies.
Combine and blend ingredients and place in baking dish.

title: mary tom's chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine and set aside.
Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to first mixture and pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together.
Use 1 to 2 tablespoons to a cup of hot water for a serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Blend soup, sour cream, water and parsley. Alternate potatoes and sauce in a 2-quart dish.
Place chops on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: molasses cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the dry ingredients together. Put the coffee in the refrigerator to chill.
Mix all the other wet ingredients together.
Mix dry and wet ingredients together.
Take cup of coffee and dump in with other ingredients.
Mix it for two minutes.
Grease a cake pan well and then flour it.
Put the batter in the pan.
Place in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour syrup over crackers and nuts.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour on wax paper and break apart.
Cool.

title: mrs. nixon's chicken salad
directions: Combine all but last 3 items and place in large baking dish. Cover with the grated cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, add the potato chips and the almonds.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole and set casserole in a pan of water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: creamy dijon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and cook over low heat until desired consistency.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and slice.
Cut cheese into 1-inch cubes.
In casserole dish, put layer of potatoes, sausage and cheese until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese. Pour 1/2 cup of milk over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon meringue
directions: Dilute cornstarch in cold water.
Put all ingredients, except egg yolks, in pan and cook until thick.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten, and cook again.
Cool; pour into baked pie shell.
Use whites of eggs for meringue and brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oil. Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in the 2 tablespoons of warm water.
Add buttermilk to mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
If necessary, add additional flour to make soft dough. Roll out about 3/4 inch thickness.
Dip in melted butter and fold over to a make pocketbook rolls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or lightly browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat butter, shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Stir together flour, baking soda and baking powder; add butter mixture. Beat until well blended.
Stir in peanut butter chips.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients, except ham.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add ham and heat 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
eggs, soup and milk. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart rectangular baking dish.
Bake about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
In a microwave safe bowl, heat vanilla chips and oil on medium high for 2 minutes, stir after 1 minute.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix well.
Spread onto wax paper-lined baking sheets.
Cool.
Break apart.
Store in an airtight container. This recipe freezes well.

title: peanut chocolate banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray bottom of 2 loaf pans (8 x 4 inches).
Combine flour and sugar.
Add bananas, milk, peanut butter, applesauce, and egg; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in 3/4 cup of chocolate chips.
Spoon batter into pans until 3/4 full.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup of chocolate chips evenly over batter.
Bake 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove loaf.
Cool completely and cup into slices.

title: croutons
directions: Add all ingredients to melted butter EXCEPT bread.
Stir well.
Toss bread cubes with butter mixture.
Put in large roaster pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: carrot raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer until very light and frothy, about 2 minutes.
Add sugars and continue beating, about 3 minutes.
Blend in Butter Buds.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oats, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add gradually to egg mixture.
Stir in carrots and raisins.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with Pam.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice and nuts.
Cool slightly.
Stir in ice cream, freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Coat two 4 X 8 inch pans with non-stick spray. In a large bowl, beat eggs. Stir in oil, plain yogurt, honey, zucchini and vanilla. In another bowl, whisk the flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Stir into egg mixture until well blended. Stir in raisins and nuts. Bake 40-45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauteed bean cakes with tomato salsa
directions: Mix 3 1/2 cups of the bread crumbs, the parsley, yogurt, mustard, lemon juice, onions, egg whites and beans.
Shape into 12 (3 1/2-inch) patties.
Coat patties with remaining bread crumbs. Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Cook patties in margarine 5 to 6 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with salsa.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and salt. Add eggs. Beat well. Add dry ingredients. Add bananas and nuts.
Baked in greased and floured loaf pan (or 2 small loaf pans) at 350° for 50 minutes (less time for small loaves).

title: vegetable cheddar soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour, onion powder, white pepper, milk, chicken broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Yields 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: maryland crab bisque
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan melt butter and saute celery for 5 minutes or until soft. Stir in sauce mix. Gradually stir in half and half. Add sherry and broth. Stir over low heat until soup bubbles and thickens slightly. Stir in crabmeat; simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: dad's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.
Brown 1 pound hamburger in 1 tablespoon olive oil, seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic cloves to taste.
Drain grease; add to sauce and simmer forever.

title: gourmet potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, cubes and salt.
Cove and cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup of milk and heat thoroughly.
In medium bowl, blend sour cream dip and flour.
Gradually stir in the remaining 1 cup milk.
Pour about 1/3 of hot potato mixture into sour cream mixture.
Return all to saucepan; cook and stir until thickened.
Garnish with parsley.

title: 31-day cake
directions: Day 1:
Add starter, peaches and juice.
Cut peaches into 4 pieces.
Add 2 1/2 cups of sugar.
Stir in a large gallon jar for 10 days.

title: cold biscuit pudding
directions: Beat egg, then add vanilla, sugar and milk; mix good.
Add biscuits.
Set oven at 400° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Before putting in oven, spread butter on top.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 - 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Line the bottom of each pan with aluminum foil.
In a large bowl mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt. Make a well in the center of this mixture and pour eggs and oil in the well.
Stir until dry ingredients just become moist. Pour thawed strawberries and juice into a container.
With a slotted spoon, dip out strawberries and gently stir into the above mixture. Then add juice gradually stirring until batter is of the proper consistency.
The amount of juice varies in strawberries when thawed.
You do not want the batter to be too thin.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tested done with a toothpick and the pick comes out clean.
Let cool in pans 15 minutes.
With a knife loosen sides of loaves from pans.
Turn out of pans.
Let loaves cool completely before slicing.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: 2 of love and caring,

title: spaghetti squash with sauce
directions: Boil squash until tender; place on platter.
Saute onions and garlic until tender in oil; add beef and other ingredients. When cooked, pour over squash.

title: homemade mints
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and a little milk, flavor to taste. Add just enough milk so you can press through icing tube.
Color to suit occasion.
Better not made too far ahead as they may dry out some.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix margarine and oatmeal.
Add Karo, brown sugar, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes in greased pan.* Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over mixture.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate over top and top with chopped walnuts. Cut and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Stuff turkey; rub outside with bacon fat or oleo and salt. Place in extra large brown paper bag.
Seal opening securely with a wire tie.
Place in roasting pan in cold oven.
Bake at 500° for first hour, 400° for second hour and 300° for third hour.
With this method, the turkey is always done to perfection, whether it's 12 pounds or 24 pounds.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate

title: grandma's oatmeal bread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine boiling water, butter, salt and sugar.
Stir in oats; cool to lukewarm.
In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in molasses, brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add oat mixture and enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and allow to rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down; divide in half and shape into balls. Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place in two greased 1 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until nearly doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil the last 20 minutes if loaves are browning excessively.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix ground walnuts, flour and stick of butter or margarine. Mix and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown, about 10 minutes; cool completely.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie pan. Beat eggs slightly.
Pour milk mixture into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven to 300° and bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: wonderful crusty rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put 1 tablespoon in each miniature muffin tin (does not work well for regular size muffin tins).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can reheat (in muffin tins) at 250° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill 3 to 4 hours, then shape into 1-inch balls. Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place rice in sprayed 9 x 13 baking pan. Pour 1 cup water around outside of Minute rice. Arrange chicken pieces over rice. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon evenly over chicken. Cover and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: refrigerator peach jell-o cake
directions: Mix the yellow cake mix according to package directions and bake.
When cake is done and still hot, poke holes all over with a fork.
Prepare a box of peach Jell-O using 2 cups of boiling water and stir until all Jell-O is dissolved.
(Do not add any cold water to this.)
Pour the hot Jell-O over the cake and let cool completely.
Prepare the topping recipe and spread over cake. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: lina's famous french toast
directions: First get the first 3 ingredients and beat together with fork. Meanwhile, you have your griddle or large frying pan on the stove with a tiny bit of butter heating up.
Dip your bread in batter on both sides; continue to do the same until the bread and batter is used up.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes more.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cakes 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add remainder of ingredients, except half the dressing mix.
Mix well. Mix remainder dressing mix with 1 stick soft oleo.
Line baking dish with dressing mixture; reserve small amount to sprinkle on top. Fill dish with squash.
Cover with reserved dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Place cereal in a large pan. Melt chips and peanut butter. Gently stir into cereal, using
powdered sugar so that it doesn't stick.

title: energy bars
directions: Melt together first 5 ingredients, stirring over low heat until marshmallows are melted. Add Rice Krispies and vanilla. Place in foil-lined pan and cool thoroughly. Cut into squares. Store in plastic container.
Makes 24 squares.

title: buttermilk biscuits and honey butter
directions: Mix in small bowl.
Beat in honey and nutmeg.
Cover and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: molded pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over Jell-O.
Mix.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.
Shape level measuring tablespoons of dough into balls.
Roll in corn flakes. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top with quartered cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Put sugar and cinnamon in
a
shaker
bag
and add biscuits. Shake until biscuits are completely covered.
Melt the stick of margarine.	Layer
Bundt
pan
with
biscuits and add remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture
to melted butter.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350°
until
biscuits
are	brown.	This is great for breakfast.	(Cooking time:	25 minutes.)

title: shortening bread(this is a quick recipe to do, and children love it!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Press into different shapes, such as moon, square or heart and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chip dip
directions: Blend and store in refrigerator.

title: hawaiian barbecue ribs
directions: Cover ribs with water and cook until tender. Drain. Put ribs in a baking dish. In a separate bowl, mix all ingredients together. Pour over ribs. Marinate for 1 hour. Bake in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour or until sauce thickens or brown over charcoal.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Place chicken in shallow glass container.
In bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whipped topping. After mixing well, fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: souperburger sandwiches
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, ketchup and pepper. Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve on buns.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble up bread in bowl.
Add diced celery and onion to bread.
Add pepper and sage.
Mix all together, then add broth to mixture until bread is very moist.
Pour in baking dish or add to your chicken or turkey and bake.

title: applesauce-banana-date-raisin dietetic cookies
directions: Combine dates, water and raisins; boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream together eggs, sweetener, margarine, vanilla, bananas, apple butter and applesauce.
Sift together flour, spices and soda.
Combine three mixtures together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
These are very tasty!

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and meal.
Add butter, lemon juice, sweet milk and grated rind of lemon.
Add the eggs and beat really well with mixer.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: bourbon dogs (wieners)
directions: Combine wieners and rest of ingredients in a bowl and marinate 4 hours. Place mixture in a saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes. Then transfer to a chafing dish to serve.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix margarine, sugar, orange juice and cornstarch.
Pour over apples.
Put a top pie crust over apple mixture.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken potato soup
directions: Bring the water to a boil.
Add mixed Veg-All and bring to a boil.
Add hash browns, bouillon cubes and onion.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add milk, cream of chicken soup, cheese and pepper. Stir until cheese melts.
Add cooked and cubed chicken.
Stir and serve.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together coconut
and
nuts;
press
into
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix
cake according to directions on box and pour over the coconut
and
nuts.
Heat margarine and cream cheese until warm enough to mix with confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white hill cafe barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Add onion, salt, pepper, paprika, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Blend well.
Cook until barbecue is hot and serve over rolls.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook pie shell about 5 minutes.
Mix in all ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo. Add the mushrooms, soups, milk, cheese, Tabasco and pimento. Simmer sauce until cheese is melted. Then layer in baking dish the chicken, canned asparagus (well drained) and sauce. Repeat, ending with sauce. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top to look finished. Bake at 350° until it bubbles. FREEZES GREAT!!!!

title: almond date surprise
directions: Mix vanilla and baking powder in beaten egg whites.
Add egg white mixture to rest of ingredients.
Bake in an 8-inch greased pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream, or Cool Whip.

title: corn and hamburger skillet
directions: Brown beef and onions; add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until onions are tender and beef is thoroughly cooked.
Drain. Add corn, potatoes and butter; heat thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix together all ingredients. Add milk for a creamy consistency. If more sugar is desired, add brown sugar. Good served with sliced Granny Smith apples.

title: real orange cookies
directions: Start heating oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix shortening with sugar, eggs and orange rind until creamy.
Mix in flour mixture alternately with orange juice. Mix in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon (2-inches apart) onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broiled red fish lafitte
directions: Season red fish on both sides and lightly flour.
Broil in butter and pour lemon juice on fish when done; keep warm.
Place butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until light brown.
Add crawfish, lobster base and water.
Bring to a boil, then add all other ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve seafood mixture over fish.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: In large heavy skillet, make roux by heating cooking oil and flour until dark brown. Stir in onions and bell pepper. Cook until tender, about 5 minutes. Add mushroom soup, onion soup and crawfish fat. Add crawfish and season to taste. Cover and cook on low heat for 60 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and add 1 can coconut.
Bake.
Cool.
Poke holes in cake.
Shake can of creamed coconut and pour over cake evenly.
Put in refrigerator 2 hours after icing cake with 1 small container of Cool Whip mixed with 3/4 cup coconut.
This is a very moist cake.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil first five ingredients together and then pour over cooked, shelled hard-boiled eggs.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, drain.
Add milk and vegetables. Bring to a gentle boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese, margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted and vegetables are tender.
Ingredients can be doubled.

title: steak and sweet pepper saute
directions: Select a standing prime roast which is well trimmed with ribs cut to desired length.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Sift flour with salt and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon into a large bowl.
Add brown sugar, sugar and salad oil.
Mix on medium speed until well blended. Take out 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping; add nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and mix; set aside.

title: mushroom stuffings
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish place chopped stems and onion. Cover.
Microwave at High (10) 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes. To hot mixture add cream cheese, mashing and mixing well.
Stir in crumbs and ham or bacon.
Stuffs 12 large mushrooms.

title: cheesecake #2
directions: Use a 9-inch pan.
Put in some graham cracker crumbs and swirl them around until they coat the pan.
Break up the cream cheese in a large bowl.
Leave it until it reaches room temperature.
Whip the cream cheese.
Add flour, salt and sugar gradually.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind, sour cream, heavy cream and vanilla to mixture. Add eggs, one at a time, until each is blended.
Fold in 3 whipped egg whites.
Flash heat at 450° for 12 minutes.
(Place a pan of water in oven to prevent cake from burning.)
Drop oven temperature to 250° for 50 minutes.
Top with your favorite topping.

title: one pan magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and pecans. Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: papa rellenas(meat filled potato balls)
directions: Boil and mash potatoes with butter and milk and put aside. Combine all other ingredients with chopped meat and saute until brown.
Take mashed potatoes and form a medium sized ball.
Put 1 tablespoon meat and press into center and surround with mashed potatoes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat at high speed for 6 minutes.
Put in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutty-buttery pies
directions: Cream cheese, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Sprinkle with salted nuts and drizzle with syrup.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions with butter in a saucepan.
Add garlic salt, as much as desired.
Pour in chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add rice; stir, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add more butter, if desired.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients and let boil until thickened.
Remove from heat and serve over hot biscuits.

title: korean mon-du
directions: Boil spinach and bean sprouts.
Dice onions.
Chop beef thinly.
Combine cooked vegetables, bean cake and beef.
Chop finely together.
Add sesame oil until mixture can make a ball. Add salt and pepper and mix more.
Put small mound on Mon-Du or egg roll square and make rectangle.
Seal edges tightly together with water.
Steam until dough is tender.
Dip in soy sauce and vinegar to taste.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Arrange the peppers in a greased 10-inch pie plate. Cover with the cheese. Pour eggs over the cheese. Bake at 275° for approximately 40 minutes or until set. Cut into small wedges and serve hot.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: With your mixer, mix this well.
Spread on English muffin quarters.
Now here's the secret; the most important step is you must freeze them at least 30 minutes.
When your guests arrive, broil them until they puff up and are bubbly and slightly golden brown.
They just take a few minutes.
Serve hot and listen to everyone carry on about them.
It just takes 10 minutes to make these 48 hot canapes that melt in your mouth.
Keep a supply in your freezer and you're ready for unexpected guests.
Also, excellent to serve with soup or a salad.
